203 // As a subroutine for NCS, NEURON simulates the cells of a subnet
204 // (usually a single cell) and NCS manages whatever intercellular
205 // NetCon connections were specified by the hoc cvode method
206 // Cvode.ncs_netcons(List nc_inlist, List nc_outlist) . The former list
207 // is normally in one to one correspondence with all the synapses. These
208 // NetCon objects have those synapses as targets and nullptr sources.
209 // The latter list is normally in one to one correspondence with
210 // the cells of the subnet. Those NetCon objects have sources of the form
211 // cell.axon.v(1) and nullptr targets.
212 // Note that the program that creates the hoc file knows
213 // how to tell NCS that a particular integer corresponds to a particular
214 // NetCon
215

335 DiscreteEvent* PlayRecordEvent::savestate_read(FILE* f) {
336  char buf[100];
337  int type, plr_index;
338  nrn_assert(fgets(buf, 100, f));
339  sscanf(buf, "%d %d\n", &type, &plr_index);

349 PlayRecordSave* PlayRecord::savestate_read(FILE* f) {
350  PlayRecordSave* prs = nullptr;
351  int type, index;
352  char buf[100];
353  nrn_assert(fgets(buf, 100, f));
354  nrn_assert(sscanf(buf, "%d %d\n", &type, &index) == 2);
355  PlayRecord* plr = net_cvode_instance->playrec_item(index);
356  assert(plr->type() == type);
357  switch (type) {
358  case VecRecordDiscreteType:
359  prs = new VecRecordDiscreteSave(plr);
360  break;
361  case VecRecordDtType:
362  prs = new VecRecordDtSave(plr);
363  break;
364  case VecPlayStepType:
365  prs = new VecPlayStepSave(plr);
366  break;
367  case VecPlayContinuousType:
368  prs = new VecPlayContinuousSave(plr);
369  break;
370  default:
371  // whenever there is no subclass specific data to save
372  prs = new PlayRecordSave(plr);
373  break;
374  }
375  prs->savestate_read(f);
376  return prs;
377 }

441 static double nc_preloc(void* v) { // user must pop section stack after call
442  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
443  Section* s = nullptr;
444  if (d->src_) {
445  s = d->src_->ssrc_;
446  }
447  if (s) {
448  nrn_pushsec(s);
449  // This is a special handle, not just a pointer.
450  auto const& v = d->src_->thvar_;
451  nrn_parent_info(s); // make sure parentnode exists
452  // there is no efficient search for the location of
453  // an arbitrary variable. Search only for v at 0 - 1.
454  // Otherwise return .5 .
455  if (v == s->parentnode->v_handle()) {
456  return nrn_arc_position(s, s->parentnode);
457  }
458  for (int i = 0; i < s->nnode; ++i) {
459  if (v == s->pnode[i]->v_handle()) {
460  return nrn_arc_position(s, s->pnode[i]);
461  }
462  }
463  return -2.; // not voltage
464  } else {
465  return -1.;
466  }
467 }
468 
469 static Object** nc_preseg(void* v) { // user must pop section stack after call
470  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
471  Section* s = NULL;
472  Object* obj = NULL;
473  double x = -1.;
474  if (d->src_) {
475  s = d->src_->ssrc_;
476  }
477  if (s && nrnpy_seg_from_sec_x) {
478  auto const& v = d->src_->thvar_;
479  nrn_parent_info(s); // make sure parentnode exists
480  // there is no efficient search for the location of
481  // an arbitrary variable. Search only for v at 0 - 1.
482  // Otherwise return NULL.
483  if (v == s->parentnode->v_handle()) {
484  x = nrn_arc_position(s, s->parentnode);
485  }
486  for (int i = 0; i < s->nnode; ++i) {
487  if (v == s->pnode[i]->v_handle()) {
488  x = nrn_arc_position(s, s->pnode[i]);
489  continue;
490  }
491  }
492  // perhaps should search for v
493  if (x >= 0) {
494  obj = (*nrnpy_seg_from_sec_x)(s, x);
495  --obj->refcount;
496  }
497  }
498  return hoc_temp_objptr(obj);
499 }
500 
501 static double nc_postloc(void* v) { // user must pop section stack after call
502  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
503  if (d->target_ && d->target_->sec) {
504  nrn_pushsec(d->target_->sec);
505  return nrn_arc_position(d->target_->sec, d->target_->node);
506  } else {
507  return -1.;
508  }
509 }
510 
511 static Object** nc_postseg(void* v) { // user must pop section stack after call
512  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
513  Object* obj = NULL;
514  if (d->target_ && d->target_->sec && nrnpy_seg_from_sec_x) {
515  double x = nrn_arc_position(d->target_->sec, d->target_->node);
516  obj = (*nrnpy_seg_from_sec_x)(d->target_->sec, x);
517  --obj->refcount;
518  }
519  return hoc_temp_objptr(obj);
520 }

540 static Object** newoclist(int i, OcList*& o) {
541  Object** po;
542  if (ifarg(i) && hoc_is_object_arg(i)) {
543  po = hoc_objgetarg(i);
544  check_obj_type(*po, "List");
545  o = (OcList*) ((*po)->u.this_pointer);
546  } else {
547  o = new OcList();
548  o->ref();
549  Symbol* sl = hoc_lookup("List");
550  po = hoc_temp_objvar(sl, o);
551  }
552  return po;
553 }

555 static Object** nc_prelist(void* v) {
556  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
557  OcList* o;
558  Object** po = newoclist(1, o);
559  if (d->src_) {
560  for (const auto& nc: d->src_->dil_) {
561  if (nc->obj_) {
562  o->append(nc->obj_);
563  }
564  }
565  }
566  return po;
567 }
568 
569 static Object** nc_synlist(void* v) {
570  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
571  OcList* o;
572  Object** po = newoclist(1, o);
573  hoc_Item* q;
574  if (net_cvode_instance->psl_)
575  ITERATE(q, net_cvode_instance->psl_) {
576  PreSyn* ps = (PreSyn*) VOIDITM(q);
577  for (const auto& nc: ps->dil_) {
578  if (nc->obj_ && nc->target_ == d->target_) {
579  o->append(nc->obj_);
580  }
581  }
582  }
583  return po;
584 }

586 static Object** nc_postcelllist(void* v) {
587  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
588  OcList* o;
589  Object** po = newoclist(1, o);
590  hoc_Item* q;
591  Object* cell = nullptr;
592  if (d->target_ && d->target_->sec) {
593  cell = nrn_sec2cell(d->target_->sec);
594  }
595  if (cell && net_cvode_instance->psl_)
596  ITERATE(q, net_cvode_instance->psl_) {
597  PreSyn* ps = (PreSyn*) VOIDITM(q);
598  for (const auto& nc: ps->dil_) {
599  if (nc->obj_ && nc->target_ && nrn_sec2cell_equals(nc->target_->sec, cell)) {
600  o->append(nc->obj_);
601  }
602  }
603  }
604  return po;
605 }

607 static Object** nc_precelllist(void* v) {
608  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
609  OcList* o;
610  Object** po = newoclist(1, o);
611  hoc_Item* q;
612  Object* cell = nullptr;
613  if (d->src_ && d->src_->ssrc_) {
614  cell = nrn_sec2cell(d->src_->ssrc_);
615  }
616  if (cell && net_cvode_instance->psl_)
617  ITERATE(q, net_cvode_instance->psl_) {
618  PreSyn* ps = (PreSyn*) VOIDITM(q);
619  for (const auto& nc: ps->dil_) {
620  if (nc->obj_ && nc->src_ && ps->ssrc_ && nrn_sec2cell_equals(ps->ssrc_, cell)) {
621  o->append(nc->obj_);
622  }
623  }
624  }
625  return po;
626 }

628 static Object** nc_precell(void* v) {
629  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
630  if (d->src_ && d->src_->ssrc_) {
631  return hoc_temp_objptr(nrn_sec2cell(d->src_->ssrc_));
632  } else {
633  return hoc_temp_objptr(0);
634  }
635 }
636 
637 static Object** nc_postcell(void* v) {
638  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
639  Object* ob = nullptr;
640  if (d->target_ && d->target_->sec) {
641  ob = nrn_sec2cell(d->target_->sec);
642  }
643  return hoc_temp_objptr(ob);
644 }
645 
646 static double nc_setpost(void* v) {
647  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
648  Object* otar = nullptr;
649  if (ifarg(1)) {
650  otar = *hoc_objgetarg(1);
651  }
652  if (otar && !is_point_process(otar)) {
653  hoc_execerror("argument must be a point process or NULLobject", 0);
654  }
655  Point_process* tar = nullptr;
656  if (otar) {
657  tar = ob2pntproc(otar);
658  }
659  if (d->target_ && d->target_ != tar) {
660 #if DISCRETE_EVENT_OBSERVER
661  ObjObservable::Detach(d->target_->ob, d);
662 #endif
663  d->target_ = nullptr;
664  }
665  int cnt = 1;
666  if (tar) {
667  cnt = pnt_receive_size[tar->prop->_type];
668  d->target_ = tar;
669 #if DISCRETE_EVENT_OBSERVER
670  ObjObservable::Attach(otar, d);
671 #endif
672  } else {
673  d->active_ = false;
674  }
675  if (d->cnt_ != cnt) {
676  d->cnt_ = cnt;
677  delete[] std::exchange(d->weight_, new double[d->cnt_]);
678  }
679  return 0.;
680 }
681 
682 static double nc_valid(void* v) {
683  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
684  hoc_return_type_code = 2;
685  if (d->src_ && d->target_) {
686  return 1.;
687  }
688  return 0.;
689 }
690 
691 static double nc_active(void* v) {
692  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
693  bool a = d->active_;
694  if (d->target_ && ifarg(1)) {
695  d->active_ = bool(chkarg(1, 0, 1));
696  }
697  hoc_return_type_code = 2;
698  return double(a);
699 }
700 
701 // for threads, revised net_send to use absolute time (in the
702 // mod file we add the thread time when we call it).
703 // And we can no longer check with respect to minimum time in chkarg
704 static double nc_event(void* v) {
705  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
706  double td = chkarg(1, -1e20, 1e20);
707  if (d->active_ == 0) {
708  return 0.0;
709  }
710  d->chktar();
711  NrnThread* nt = PP2NT(d->target_);
712  const auto nrn_thread_not_initialized_for_nc_target = nt && nt >= nrn_threads &&
713  nt < (nrn_threads + nrn_nthread);
714  nrn_assert(nrn_thread_not_initialized_for_nc_target);
715  if (ifarg(2)) {
716  double flag = *getarg(2);
717  Point_process* pnt = d->target_;
718  int type = pnt->prop->_type;
719  if (!nrn_is_artificial_[type]) {
720  hoc_execerror("Can only send fake self-events to ARTIFICIAL_CELLs", 0);
721  }
722  auto* pq = pnt->prop->dparam + nrn_artcell_qindex_[type];
723  nrn_net_send(pq, d->weight_, pnt, td, flag);
724  } else {
725  net_cvode_instance->event(td, d, PP2NT(d->target_));
726  }
727  return (double) d->active_;
728 }
729 static double nc_record(void* v) {
730  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
731  d->chksrc();
732  if (ifarg(1)) {
733  if (ifarg(2)) {
734  int recid = d->obj_->index;
735  if (ifarg(3)) {
736  recid = (int) (*getarg(3));
737  }
738  d->src_->record(vector_arg(1), vector_arg(2), recid);
739  } else if (hoc_is_str_arg(1)) {
740  d->src_->record_stmt(gargstr(1));
741  } else if (is_vector_arg(1)) {
742  d->src_->record(vector_arg(1));
743  } else {
744  d->src_->record_stmt(*hoc_objgetarg(1));
745  }
746  } else {
747  d->src_->record(nullptr);
748  }
749  return 0;
750 }
751 
752 static double nc_srcgid(void* v) {
753  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
754  hoc_return_type_code = 1;
755  if (d->src_) {
756  return (double) d->src_->gid_;
757  }
758  return -1.;
759 }

764  if (d->src_ && d->src_->tvec_) {
765  ob = d->src_->tvec_->obj_;
766  }
767  return hoc_temp_objptr(ob);
768 }

803 static void steer_val(void* v) {
804  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
805  Symbol* s = hoc_spop();
806  if (strcmp(s->name, "delay") == 0) {
807  d->chksrc();
808  hoc_pushpx(&d->delay_);
809  d->src_->use_min_delay_ = 0;
810  } else if (strcmp(s->name, "weight") == 0) {
811  int index = 0;
812  if (hoc_stack_type_is_ndim()) {
813  s->arayinfo->sub[0] = d->cnt_;
814  index = hoc_araypt(s, SYMBOL);
815  }
816  hoc_pushpx(d->weight_ + index);
817  } else if (strcmp(s->name, "x") == 0) {
818  static double dummy = 0.;
819  d->chksrc();
820  if (d->src_->thvar_) {
821  hoc_push(d->src_->thvar_);
822  } else {
823  dummy = 0.;
824  hoc_pushpx(&dummy);
825  }
826  } else if (strcmp(s->name, "threshold") == 0) {
827  d->chksrc();
828  hoc_pushpx(&d->src_->threshold_);
829  }
830 }
831 
832 static void* cons(Object* o) {
833  NetCon* d;
834  if (!net_cvode_instance) {
835  hoc_execerror("CVode instance must exist", 0);
836  }
837  // source, target, threshold, delay, magnitude
838  Object *osrc = nullptr, *otar;
839  Section* srcsec = nullptr;
840  neuron::container::data_handle<double> psrc{};
841  if (hoc_is_object_arg(1)) {
842  osrc = *hoc_objgetarg(1);
843  if (osrc && !is_point_process(osrc)) {
844  hoc_execerror("if arg 1 is an object it must be a point process or NULLObject", 0);
845  }
846  } else {
847  psrc = hoc_hgetarg<double>(1);
848  srcsec = chk_access();
849  }
850  otar = *hoc_objgetarg(2);
851  if (otar && !is_point_process(otar)) {
852  hoc_execerror("arg 2 must be a point process or NULLobject", 0);
853  }
854  double thresh = -1.e9; // sentinal value. default is 10 if new PreSyn
855  double delay = 1.;
856  double weight = 0.;
857 
858  if (ifarg(3)) {
859  thresh = *getarg(3);
860  delay = chkarg(4, 0, 1e15);
861  weight = *getarg(5);
862  }
863  d = net_cvode_instance->install_deliver(psrc, srcsec, osrc, otar, thresh, delay, weight);
864  d->obj_ = o;
865  return (void*) d;
866 }
867 
868 static void destruct(void* v) {
869  delete static_cast<NetCon*>(v);
870 }

872 void NetCon_reg() {
873  class2oc("NetCon", cons, destruct, members, NULL, omembers, NULL);
874  Symbol* nc = hoc_lookup("NetCon");
875  nc->u.ctemplate->steer = steer_val;
876  Symbol* s;
877  s = hoc_table_lookup("delay", nc->u.ctemplate->symtable);
878  s->type = VAR;
879  s->arayinfo = nullptr;
880  s = hoc_table_lookup("x", nc->u.ctemplate->symtable);
881  s->type = VAR;
882  s->arayinfo = nullptr;
883  s = hoc_table_lookup("threshold", nc->u.ctemplate->symtable);
884  s->type = VAR;
885  s->arayinfo = nullptr;
886  s = hoc_table_lookup("weight", nc->u.ctemplate->symtable);
887  s->type = VAR;
888  s->arayinfo = new Arrayinfo;
889  s->arayinfo->refcount = 1;
890  s->arayinfo->a_varn = nullptr;
891  s->arayinfo->nsub = 1;
892  s->arayinfo->sub[0] = 1;
893 }
894 
895 static char* escape_bracket(const char* s) {
896  static char* b;
897  const char* p1;
898  char* p2;
899  if (!b) {
900  b = new char[256];
901  }
902  for (p1 = s, p2 = b; *p1; ++p1, ++p2) {
903  switch (*p1) {
904  case '<':
905  *p2 = '[';
906  break;
907  case '>':
908  *p2 = ']';
909  break;
910  case '[':
911  case ']':
912  *p2 = '\\';
913  *(++p2) = *p1;
914  break;
915  default:
916  *p2 = *p1;
917  break;
918  }
919  }
920  *p2 = '\0';
921  return b;
922 }
923 
924 Object** NetCvode::netconlist() {
925  // interface to cvode.netconlist(precell, postcell, target, [list])
926  OcList* o;
927 
928  Object** po = newoclist(4, o);
929 
930  Object *opre = nullptr, *opost = nullptr, *otar = nullptr;
931  std::regex spre, spost, star;
932 
933  if (hoc_is_object_arg(1)) {
934  opre = *hoc_objgetarg(1);
935  } else {
936  std::string s(gargstr(1));
937  if (s.empty()) {
938  spre = std::regex(".*");
939  } else {
940  try {
941  spre = std::regex(escape_bracket(s.data()));
942  } catch (std::regex_error&) {
943  hoc_execerror(gargstr(1), "not a valid regular expression");
944  }
945  }
946  }
947  if (hoc_is_object_arg(2)) {
948  opost = *hoc_objgetarg(2);
949  } else {
950  std::string s(gargstr(2));
951  if (s.empty()) {
952  spost = std::regex(".*");
953  } else {
954  try {
955  spost = std::regex(escape_bracket(s.data()));
956  } catch (std::regex_error&) {
957  hoc_execerror(gargstr(2), "not a valid regular expression");
958  }
959  }
960  }
961  if (hoc_is_object_arg(3)) {
962  otar = *hoc_objgetarg(3);
963  } else {
964  std::string s(gargstr(3));
965  if (s.empty()) {
966  star = std::regex(".*");
967  } else {
968  try {
969  star = std::regex(escape_bracket(s.data()));
970  } catch (std::regex_error&) {
971  hoc_execerror(gargstr(3), "not a valid regular expression");
972  }
973  }
974  }
975 
976  hoc_Item* q;
977  if (psl_) {
978  ITERATE(q, psl_) {
979  PreSyn* ps = (PreSyn*) VOIDITM(q);
980  bool b = false;
981  if (ps->ssrc_) {
982  Object* precell = nrn_sec2cell(ps->ssrc_);
983  if (opre) {
984  b = precell == opre;
985  } else {
986  std::string s(hoc_object_name(precell));
987  b = std::regex_search(s, spre);
988  }
989  } else if (ps->osrc_) {
990  Object* presyn = ps->osrc_;
991  if (opre) {
992  b = presyn == opre;
993  } else {
994  std::string s(hoc_object_name(presyn));
995  b = std::regex_search(s, spre);
996  }
997  }
998  if (b) {
999  for (const auto& d: ps->dil_) {
1000  Object* postcell = nullptr;
1001  Object* target = nullptr;
1002  if (d->target_) {
1003  Point_process* p = d->target_;
1004  target = p->ob;
1005  if (p->sec) {
1006  postcell = nrn_sec2cell(p->sec);
1007  }
1008  }
1009  if (opost) {
1010  b = postcell == opost;
1011  } else {
1012  std::string s(hoc_object_name(postcell));
1013  b = std::regex_search(s, spost);
1014  }
1015  if (b) {
1016  if (otar) {
1017  b = target == otar;
1018  } else {
1019  std::string s(hoc_object_name(target));
1020  b = std::regex_search(s, star);
1021  }
1022  if (b) {
1023  o->append(d->obj_);
1024  }
1025  }
1026  }
1027  }
1028  }
1029  }
1030  return po;
1031 }

1034 NetCvodeThreadData::NetCvodeThreadData() {
1035  tpool_ = new TQItemPool(1000, 1);
1036  // tqe_ accessed only by thread i so no locking
1037  tqe_ = new TQueue(tpool_, 0);
1038  sepool_ = new SelfEventPool(1000, 1);
1039  selfqueue_ = nullptr;
1040  psl_thr_ = nullptr;
1041  tq_ = nullptr;
1042  lcv_ = nullptr;
1043  ite_size_ = ITE_SIZE;
1044  ite_cnt_ = 0;
1045  unreffed_event_cnt_ = 0;
1046  immediate_deliver_ = -1e100;

1048  nlcv_ = 0;
1049  MUTCONSTRUCT(1)
1050 }

1052 NetCvodeThreadData::~NetCvodeThreadData() {
1053  delete[] std::exchange(inter_thread_events_, nullptr);
1054  if (psl_thr_) {
1055  hoc_l_freelist(&psl_thr_);
1056  }
1057  delete std::exchange(tq_, nullptr);
1058  delete std::exchange(tqe_, nullptr);
1059  delete std::exchange(tpool_, nullptr);
1060  if (selfqueue_) {
1061  selfqueue_->remove_all();
1062  delete std::exchange(selfqueue_, nullptr);
1063  }
1064  delete std::exchange(sepool_, nullptr);
1065  if (lcv_) {
1066  for (int i = 0; i < nlcv_; ++i) {
1067  net_cvode_instance->delete_list(lcv_ + i);
1068  }
1069  delete[] std::exchange(lcv_, nullptr);
1070  }
1071  MUTDESTRUCT
1072 }

1074 void NetCvodeThreadData::interthread_send(double td, DiscreteEvent* db, NrnThread* nt) {
1075  // bin_event(td, db, nt);
1076  MUTLOCK
1077 #if PRINT_EVENT
1078  if (net_cvode_instance->print_event_) {
1079  Printf("interthread send td=%.15g DE type=%d thread=%d target=%d %s\n",
1080  td,
1081  db->type(),
1082  nt->id,
1083  (db->type() == 2) ? PP2NT(((NetCon*) db)->target_)->id : -1,
1084  (db->type() == 2) ? hoc_object_name(((NetCon*) (db))->target_->ob) : "?");
1085  }
1086 #endif
1087  if (ite_cnt_ >= ite_size_) {
1088  ite_size_ *= 2;
1089  InterThreadEvent* in = new InterThreadEvent[ite_size_];
1090  for (int i = 0; i < ite_cnt_; ++i) {
1091  in[i].de_ = inter_thread_events_[i].de_;
1092  in[i].t_ = inter_thread_events_[i].t_;
1093  }
1094  delete[] std::exchange(inter_thread_events_, in);
1095  }
1096  InterThreadEvent& ite = inter_thread_events_[ite_cnt_++];
1097  ite.de_ = db;
1098  ite.t_ = td;
1099  // race since each NetCvodeThreadData has its own lock and enqueueing_
1100  // is a NetCvode instance variable. enqueuing_ is not logically
1101  // needed but can avoid a nrn_multithread_job call in allthread_least_t
1102  // which does nothing if there are no interthread events.
1103  // int& b = net_cvode_instance->enqueueing_;
1104  // if (!b) { b = 1; }
1105  MUTUNLOCK
1106  // have decided to lock net_cvode_instance and set it
1107  net_cvode_instance->set_enqueueing();
1108 }
1109 
1110 void NetCvodeThreadData::enqueue(NetCvode* nc, NrnThread* nt) {
1111  int i;
1112  MUTLOCK
1113  for (i = 0; i < ite_cnt_; ++i) {
1114  InterThreadEvent& ite = inter_thread_events_[i];
1115 #if PRINT_EVENT
1116  if (net_cvode_instance->print_event_) {
1117  Printf("interthread enqueue td=%.15g DE type=%d thread=%d target=%d %s\n",
1118  ite.t_,
1119  ite.de_->type(),
1120  nt->id,
1121  (ite.de_->type() == 2) ? PP2NT(((NetCon*) (ite.de_))->target_)->id : -1,
1122  (ite.de_->type() == 2) ? hoc_object_name(((NetCon*) (ite.de_))->target_->ob)
1123  : "?");
1124  }
1125 #endif
1126  nc->bin_event(ite.t_, ite.de_, nt);
1127  }
1128  ite_cnt_ = 0;
1129  MUTUNLOCK
1130 }

1139  rtol_ = 0.;
1140  atol_ = 1e-3;

1183 NetCvode::~NetCvode() {
1184  MUTDESTRUCT
1185  if (net_cvode_instance == (NetCvode*) this) {
1186  net_cvode_instance = nullptr;
1187  }
1188  delete_list();
1189  p_construct(0);
1190  // and should also iterate and delete the MaxStateItem
1191  delete std::exchange(mst_, nullptr);
1192  if (psl_) {
1193  hoc_Item* q;
1194  ITERATE(q, psl_) {
1195  auto* const ps = static_cast<PreSyn*>(VOIDITM(q));
1196  std::for_each(ps->dil_.rbegin(), ps->dil_.rend(), [](NetCon*& d) {
1197  d->src_ = nullptr;
1198  delete std::exchange(d, nullptr);
1199  });
1200  delete ps;
1201  VOIDITM(q) = nullptr;
1202  }
1203  hoc_l_freelist(&psl_);
1204  }
1205  delete std::exchange(pst_, nullptr);
1206  delete std::exchange(fixed_play_, nullptr);
1207  delete std::exchange(fixed_record_, nullptr);
1208  for (auto& item: *prl_) {
1209  delete item;
1210  }
1211  delete std::exchange(prl_, nullptr);
1212  unused_presyn = nullptr;
1213  wl_list_.clear();
1214  delete std::exchange(allthread_hocevents_, nullptr);
1215 }

1225 void NetCvode::localstep(bool b) {
1226  // due to possibility of gap junctions and until the complete matrix
1227  // is analysed for block structure localstep and daspk are incompatible
1228  b = (nrn_modeltype() == 1 ? b : false); // localstep doesn't work yet with DAE's
1229 
1230  if (!b != single_) {
1231  delete_list();
1232  single_ = !b;
1233  structure_change_cnt_ = 0;
1234  use_sparse13 = 0;
1235  nrn_use_daspk_ = false;
1236  re_init(nt_t);
1237  }
1238 }
1239 
1240 bool NetCvode::use_daspk() {
1241  return (gcv_ != 0) ? gcv_->use_daspk_ : false;
1242 }
1243 
1244 void NetCvode::use_daspk(bool b) {
1245  b = (nrn_modeltype() == 2 ? true : b); // not optional if algebraic
1246  if (gcv_ && b != gcv_->use_daspk_) {
1247  delete_list();
1248  single_ = (b ? true : single_);
1249  structure_change_cnt_ = 0;
1250  nrn_use_daspk_ = b;
1251  // printf("NetCvode::use_daspk nrn_use_daspk=%d\n", nrn_use_daspk_);
1252  if (use_sparse13 != nrn_use_daspk_) {
1253  use_sparse13 = nrn_use_daspk_;
1254  diam_changed = 1;
1255  }
1256  re_init(nt_t);
1257  }
1258 }
1259 
1260 // Append new BAMechList item to arg
1261 BAMechList::BAMechList(BAMechList** first) { // preserve the list order
1262  next = nullptr;
1263  BAMechList* last;
1264  if (*first) {
1265  for (last = *first; last->next; last = last->next) {
1266  }
1267  last->next = this;
1268  } else {
1269  *first = this;
1270  }
1271 }
1272 
1273 void BAMechList::destruct(BAMechList** first) {
1274  BAMechList *b, *bn;
1275  for (b = *first; b; b = bn) {
1276  bn = b->next;
1277  delete b;
1278  }
1279  *first = nullptr;
1280 }

1321 void NetCvode::delete_list() {
1322  int i, j;
1323  wl_list_.clear();
1324  wl_list_.resize(nrn_nthread);
1325  if (gcv_) {
1326  delete_list(gcv_);
1327  delete std::exchange(gcv_, nullptr);
1328  }
1329  for (i = 0; i < pcnt_; ++i) {
1330  NetCvodeThreadData& d = p[i];
1331  if (d.lcv_) {
1332  for (j = 0; j < d.nlcv_; ++j) {
1333  delete_list(d.lcv_ + j);
1334  }
1335  delete[] std::exchange(d.lcv_, nullptr);
1336  d.nlcv_ = 0;
1337  }
1338  delete std::exchange(d.tq_, nullptr);
1339  }
1340  empty_ = true;
1341 }

1343 void NetCvode::delete_list(Cvode* cvode) {
1344  del_cv_memb_list(cvode);
1345  Cvode& cv = *cvode;
1346  cv.delete_prl();
1347  delete[] std::exchange(cv.ctd_, nullptr);
1348 }
1349 
1350 void NetCvode::del_cv_memb_list() {
1351  if (gcv_) {
1352  del_cv_memb_list(gcv_);
1353  }
1354  for (int i = 0; i < pcnt_; ++i) {
1355  NetCvodeThreadData& d = p[i];
1356  for (int j = 0; j < d.nlcv_; ++j) {
1357  del_cv_memb_list(d.lcv_ + j);
1358  }
1359  }
1360 }
1361 void NetCvode::del_cv_memb_list(Cvode* cvode) {
1362  if (!cvode) {
1363  return;
1364  }
1365  Cvode& cv = *cvode;
1366  for (int j = 0; j < cv.nctd_; ++j) {
1367  CvodeThreadData& z = cv.ctd_[j];
1368  if (z.psl_th_) {
1369  z.psl_th_->clear();
1370  delete std::exchange(z.psl_th_, nullptr);
1371  }
1372  if (cvode != gcv_) {
1373  if (z.v_node_) {
1374  delete[] std::exchange(z.v_node_, nullptr);
1375  delete[] std::exchange(z.v_parent_, nullptr);
1376  }
1377  z.delete_memb_list(std::exchange(z.cv_memb_list_, nullptr));
1378  } else {
1379  CvMembList *cml, *cmlnext;
1380  for (cml = std::exchange(z.cv_memb_list_, nullptr); cml; cml = cmlnext) {
1381  cmlnext = cml->next;
1382  delete cml;
1383  }
1384  }
1385  BAMechList::destruct(&z.before_breakpoint_);
1386  BAMechList::destruct(&z.after_solve_);
1387  BAMechList::destruct(&z.before_step_);
1388  }
1389 }
1390 
1391 void CvodeThreadData::delete_memb_list(CvMembList* cmlist) {
1392  CvMembList *cml, *cmlnext;
1393  for (cml = cmlist; cml; cml = cmlnext) {
1394  auto const& ml = cml->ml;
1395  cmlnext = cml->next;
1396  for (auto& ml: cml->ml) {
1397  delete[] std::exchange(ml.nodelist, nullptr);
1398  delete[] std::exchange(ml.nodeindices, nullptr);
1399  delete[] std::exchange(ml.prop, nullptr);
1400  if (!memb_func[cml->index].hoc_mech) {
1401  delete[] std::exchange(ml.pdata, nullptr);
1402  }
1403  }
1404  delete cml;
1405  }
1406 }
1407 
1408 void NetCvode::distribute_dinfo(int* cellnum, int tid) {
1409  int j;
1410  // printf("distribute_dinfo %d\n", pst_cnt_);
1411  if (psl_) {
1412  hoc_Item* q;
1413  ITERATE(q, psl_) {
1414  PreSyn* ps = (PreSyn*) VOIDITM(q);
1415  // printf("\tPreSyn %s\n", ps->osrc_ ? hoc_object_name(ps->osrc_):secname(ps->ssrc_));
1416  if (ps->thvar_) { // artcells and presyns for gid's not on this cpu have no threshold
1417  // check
1418  NrnThread* nt;
1419  Cvode* cvsrc;
1420  CvodeThreadData* z;
1421  // cvode instances poll which presyns
1422  if (single_) {
1423  if (ps->osrc_) {
1424  nt = (NrnThread*) ob2pntproc(ps->osrc_)->_vnt;
1425  } else if (ps->ssrc_) {
1426  nt = ps->ssrc_->pnode[0]->_nt;
1427  } else {
1428  nt = nrn_threads;
1429  }
1430  cvsrc = gcv_;
1431  z = cvsrc->ctd_ + nt->id;
1432  if (!z->psl_th_) {
1433  z->psl_th_ = new PreSynList();
1434  z->psl_th_->reserve(pst_cnt_);
1435  }
1436  z->psl_th_->push_back(ps);
1437  } else {
1438  if (ps->osrc_) {
1439  j = node(ps->osrc_)->v_node_index;
1440  nt = (NrnThread*) ob2pntproc(ps->osrc_)->_vnt;
1441  } else if (ps->ssrc_) {
1442  j = ps->ssrc_->pnode[0]->v_node_index;
1443  nt = ps->ssrc_->pnode[0]->_nt;
1444  } else {
1445  j = 0;
1446  nt = nrn_threads;
1447  }
1448  if (tid == nt->id) {
1449  cvsrc = p[tid].lcv_ + cellnum[j];
1450  z = cvsrc->ctd_;
1451  if (nt == cvsrc->nth_) {
1452  if (!z->psl_th_) {
1453  z->psl_th_ = new PreSynList();
1454  }
1455  z->psl_th_->push_back(ps);
1456  }
1457  }
1458  }
1459  }
1460  }
1461  }
1462 }
1463 
1464 void NetCvode::alloc_list() {
1465  int i;
1466  set_CVRhsFn();
1467  wl_list_.clear();
1468  wl_list_.resize(nrn_nthread);
1469  if (single_) {
1470  gcv_ = new Cvode();
1471  Cvode& cv = *gcv_;
1472  cv.ncv_ = this;
1473  cv.nctd_ = nrn_nthread;
1474  cv.ctd_ = new CvodeThreadData[cv.nctd_];
1475  } else {
1476  for (int id = 0; id < nrn_nthread; ++id) {
1477  NrnThread& nt = nrn_threads[id];
1478  NetCvodeThreadData& d = p[id];
1479  d.nlcv_ = nt.ncell;
1480  d.lcv_ = new Cvode[d.nlcv_];
1481  d.tq_ = new TQueue(d.tpool_);
1482  for (i = 0; i < d.nlcv_; ++i) {
1483  TQItem* ti = d.tq_->insert(0., d.lcv_ + i);
1484  d.lcv_[i].tqitem_ = ti;
1485  Cvode& cv = d.lcv_[i];
1486  cv.nth_ = &nt;
1487  cv.ncv_ = this;
1488  cv.nctd_ = 1;
1489  cv.ctd_ = new CvodeThreadData[cv.nctd_];
1490  }
1491  }
1492  }
1493  empty_ = false;
1494 #if USENEOSIM
1495  if (p_nrn2neosim_send)
1496  for (i = 0; i < nlist_; ++i) {
1497  p.lcv_[i].neosim_self_events_ = new TQueue();
1498  }
1499 #endif
1500 }
1501 
1502 bool NetCvode::init_global() {
1503  int i;
1504  CvMembList* cml;
1505  if (tree_changed) {
1506  setup_topology();
1507  }
1508  if (v_structure_change) {
1509  v_setup_vectors();
1510  }
1511  if (structure_change_cnt_ == structure_change_cnt) {
1512  return false;
1513  }
1514  if (diam_changed) { // need to guarantee that the matrix is allocated
1515  recalc_diam(); // for the present method
1516  }
1517  structure_change_cnt_ = structure_change_cnt;
1518  matrix_change_cnt_ = -1;
1519  playrec_change_cnt_ = 0;
1520  NrnThread* _nt;
1521  // We copy Memb_list* into cml->ml below. At the moment this CVode code
1522  // generates its own complicated set of Memb_list* that operate in
1523  // list-of-handles mode instead of referring to contiguous sets of values.
1524  // This is a shame, as it forces that list-of-handles mode to exist.
1525  // Possible alternatives could include:
1526  // - making the sorting algorithm more sophisticated so that the values that
1527  // are going to be processed together are contiguous -- this might be a
1528  // bit intricate, but it shouldn't be *too* had to assert that we get the
1529  // right answer -- and it's the only way of making sure the actual compute
1530  // kernels are cache efficient / vectorisable.
1531  // - changing the type used by this code to not be Memb_list but rather some
1532  // Memb_list_with_list_of_handles type and adding extra glue to the code
1533  // generation so that we can call into translated MOD file code using that
1534  // type
1535  // - Using a list of Memb_list with size 1 instead of a single Memb_list
1536  // that holds a list of handles?
1537  auto const cache_token = nrn_ensure_model_data_are_sorted();
1538  if (single_) {
1539  if (!gcv_ || gcv_->nctd_ != nrn_nthread) {
1540  delete_list();
1541  alloc_list();
1542  }
1543  del_cv_memb_list();
1544  Cvode& cv = *gcv_;
1545  distribute_dinfo(nullptr, 0);
1546  FOR_THREADS(_nt) {
1547  CvodeThreadData& z = cv.ctd_[_nt->id];
1548  z.rootnodecount_ = _nt->ncell;
1549  z.v_node_count_ = _nt->end;
1550  z.v_node_ = _nt->_v_node;
1551  z.v_parent_ = _nt->_v_parent;
1552 
1553  CvMembList* last = 0;
1554  for (NrnThreadMembList* tml = _nt->tml; tml; tml = tml->next) {
1555  i = tml->index;
1556  const Memb_func& mf = memb_func[i];
1557  Memb_list* ml = tml->ml;
1558  if (ml->nodecount && (i == CAP || mf.current || mf.ode_count || mf.ode_matsol ||
1559  mf.ode_spec || mf.state)) {
1560  // maintain same order (not reversed) for
1561  // singly linked list built below
1562  cml = new CvMembList{i};
1563  if (!z.cv_memb_list_) {
1564  z.cv_memb_list_ = cml;
1565  } else {
1566  last->next = cml;
1567  }
1568  last = cml;
1569  cml->next = nullptr;
1570  auto const mech_offset = cache_token.thread_cache(_nt->id).mechanism_offset.at(
1571  i);
1572  assert(mech_offset != neuron::container::invalid_row);
1573  assert(cml->ml.size() == 1);
1574  cml->ml[0].set_storage_offset(mech_offset);
1575  cml->ml[0].nodecount = ml->nodecount;
1576  // assumes cell info grouped contiguously
1577  cml->ml[0].nodelist = ml->nodelist;
1578  cml->ml[0].nodeindices = ml->nodeindices;
1579  assert(ml->prop);
1580  cml->ml[0].prop = ml->prop; // used for ode_map even when hoc_mech = false
1581  if (!mf.hoc_mech) {
1582  cml->ml[0].pdata = ml->pdata;
1583  }
1584  cml->ml[0]._thread = ml->_thread;
1585  }
1586  }
1587  fill_global_ba(_nt, BEFORE_BREAKPOINT, &z.before_breakpoint_);
1588  fill_global_ba(_nt, AFTER_SOLVE, &z.after_solve_);
1589  fill_global_ba(_nt, BEFORE_STEP, &z.before_step_);
1590  // Every point process, but not artificial cells, cause at least a retreat.
1591  // All point processes, but not artificial cells,
1592  // have the global cvode as its nvi field
1593  for (NrnThreadMembList* tml = _nt->tml; tml; tml = tml->next) {
1594  i = tml->index;
1595  const Memb_func& mf = memb_func[i];
1596  if (mf.is_point && !nrn_is_artificial_[i]) {
1597  Memb_list* ml = tml->ml;
1598  int j;
1599  for (j = 0; j < ml->nodecount; ++j) {
1600  auto& datum = mf.hoc_mech ? ml->prop[j]->dparam[1] : ml->pdata[j][1];
1601  auto* pp = datum.get<Point_process*>();
1602  pp->nvi_ = gcv_;
1603  }
1604  }
1605  }
1606  }
1607  } else { // lvardt
1608  bool b = false;
1609  if (gcv_) {
1610  b = true;
1611  }
1612  if (!b)
1613  for (i = 0; i < pcnt_; ++i) {
1614  if (p[i].nlcv_ != nrn_threads[i].ncell) {
1615  b = true;
1616  }
1617  }
1618  if (b) {
1619  delete_list();
1620  alloc_list();
1621  }
1622  del_cv_memb_list();
1623  // each node has a cell number
1624  for (int id = 0; id < nrn_nthread; ++id) {
1625  NrnThread* _nt = nrn_threads + id;
1626  NetCvodeThreadData& d = p[id];
1627  if (_nt->end == 0) {
1628  continue;
1629  }
1630  std::vector<int> cellnum(_nt->end);
1631  for (i = 0; i < _nt->ncell; ++i) {
1632  cellnum[i] = i;
1633  }
1634  for (i = _nt->ncell; i < _nt->end; ++i) {
1635  cellnum[i] = cellnum[_nt->_v_parent[i]->v_node_index];
1636  }
1637 
1638  for (i = 0; i < _nt->ncell; ++i) {
1639  d.lcv_[i].ctd_[0].v_node_count_ = 0;
1640  }
1641  for (i = 0; i < _nt->end; ++i) {
1642  ++d.lcv_[cellnum[i]].ctd_[0].v_node_count_;
1643  }
1644  for (i = 0; i < _nt->ncell; ++i) {
1645  d.lcv_[cellnum[i]].ctd_[0].v_node_ =
1646  new Node*[d.lcv_[cellnum[i]].ctd_[0].v_node_count_];
1647  d.lcv_[cellnum[i]].ctd_[0].v_parent_ =
1648  new Node*[d.lcv_[cellnum[i]].ctd_[0].v_node_count_];
1649  }
1650  for (i = 0; i < _nt->ncell; ++i) {
1651  d.lcv_[i].ctd_[0].v_node_count_ = 0;
1652  d.lcv_[i].ctd_[0].rootnodecount_ = 1;
1653  }
1654  for (i = 0; i < _nt->end; ++i) {
1655  d.lcv_[cellnum[i]].ctd_[0].v_node_[d.lcv_[cellnum[i]].ctd_[0].v_node_count_] =
1656  _nt->_v_node[i];
1657  d.lcv_[cellnum[i]].ctd_[0].v_parent_[d.lcv_[cellnum[i]].ctd_[0].v_node_count_++] =
1658  _nt->_v_parent[i];
1659  }
1660  // divide the memb_list info into per cell info
1661  // count
1662  std::vector<CvMembList*> last(_nt->ncell);
1663 
1664  // Need to determine if a Memb_list needs to be included
1665  // in CvMembList because there is a BEFORE/AFTER
1666  // statement that needs to be handled.
1667  std::unordered_set<int> ba_candidate;
1668  {
1669  constexpr std::array batypes{BEFORE_STEP, BEFORE_BREAKPOINT, AFTER_SOLVE};
1670  for (auto const bat: batypes) {
1671  for (BAMech* bam = bamech_[bat]; bam; bam = bam->next) {
1672  ba_candidate.insert(bam->type);
1673  }
1674  }
1675  }
1676 
1677  for (NrnThreadMembList* tml = _nt->tml; tml; tml = tml->next) {
1678  i = tml->index;
1679  const Memb_func& mf = memb_func[i];
1680  Memb_list* ml = tml->ml;
1681  if (ml->nodecount && (mf.current || mf.ode_count || mf.ode_matsol || mf.ode_spec ||
1682  mf.state || i == CAP || ba_candidate.count(i) == 1)) {
1683  // maintain same order (not reversed) for
1684  // singly linked list built below
1685  int j;
1686  for (j = 0; j < ml->nodecount; ++j) {
1687  int inode = ml->nodelist[j]->v_node_index;
1688  Cvode& cv = d.lcv_[cellnum[inode]];
1689  CvodeThreadData& z = cv.ctd_[0];
1690  if (!z.cv_memb_list_) {
1691  cml = new CvMembList{i};
1692  cml->next = nullptr;
1693  assert(cml->ml.size() == 1);
1694  cml->ml[0].nodecount = 0;
1695  z.cv_memb_list_ = cml;
1696  last[cellnum[inode]] = cml;
1697  }
1698  if (last[cellnum[inode]]->index == i) {
1699  assert(last[cellnum[inode]]->ml.size() == 1);
1700  ++last[cellnum[inode]]->ml[0].nodecount;
1701  } else {
1702  cml = new CvMembList{i};
1703  last[cellnum[inode]]->next = cml;
1704  cml->next = nullptr;
1705  last[cellnum[inode]] = cml;
1706  assert(cml->ml.size() == 1);
1707  cml->ml[0].nodecount = 1;
1708  }
1709  }
1710  }
1711  }
1712  // allocate and re-initialize count
1713  std::vector<CvMembList*> cvml(d.nlcv_);
1714  for (i = 0; i < d.nlcv_; ++i) {
1715  cvml[i] = d.lcv_[i].ctd_[0].cv_memb_list_;
1716  for (cml = cvml[i]; cml; cml = cml->next) {
1717  // non-contiguous mode, so we're going to create a lot of 1-element Memb_list
1718  // inside cml->ml
1719  cml->ml.reserve(cml->ml[0].nodecount);
1720  // remove the single entry from contiguous mode
1721  cml->ml.clear();
1722  }
1723  }
1724  // fill pointers (and nodecount)
1725  // now list order is from 0 to n_memb_func
1726  for (NrnThreadMembList* tml = _nt->tml; tml; tml = tml->next) {
1727  i = tml->index;
1728  const Memb_func& mf = memb_func[i];
1729  Memb_list* ml = tml->ml;
1730  if (ml->nodecount && (mf.current || mf.ode_count || mf.ode_matsol || mf.ode_spec ||
1731  mf.state || i == CAP || ba_candidate.count(i) == 1)) {
1732  for (int j = 0; j < ml->nodecount; ++j) {
1733  int icell = cellnum[ml->nodelist[j]->v_node_index];
1734  if (cvml[icell]->index != i) {
1735  cvml[icell] = cvml[icell]->next;
1736  assert(cvml[icell] && cvml[icell]->index);
1737  }
1738  cml = cvml[icell];
1739  auto& newml = cml->ml.emplace_back(cml->index /* mechanism type */);
1740  newml.nodecount = 1;
1741  newml.nodelist = new Node*[1];
1742  newml.nodelist[0] = ml->nodelist[j];
1743  newml.nodeindices = new int[1]{ml->nodeindices[j]};
1744  newml.prop = new Prop* [1] { ml->prop[j] };
1745  if (!mf.hoc_mech) {
1746  newml.set_storage_offset(ml->get_storage_offset() + j);
1747  newml.pdata = new Datum* [1] { ml->pdata[j] };
1748  }
1749  newml._thread = ml->_thread;
1750  }
1751  }
1752  }
1753  // do the above for the BEFORE/AFTER functions
1754  fill_local_ba(cellnum.data(), d);
1755 
1756  distribute_dinfo(cellnum.data(), id);
1757  // If a point process is not an artificial cell, fill its nvi_ field.
1758  // artifical cells have no integrator
1759  for (NrnThreadMembList* tml = _nt->tml; tml; tml = tml->next) {
1760  i = tml->index;
1761  const Memb_func& mf = memb_func[i];
1762  if (mf.is_point) {
1763  Memb_list* ml = tml->ml;
1764  int j;
1765  for (j = 0; j < ml->nodecount; ++j) {
1766  auto& datum = mf.hoc_mech ? ml->prop[j]->dparam[1] : ml->pdata[j][1];
1767  auto* pp = datum.get<Point_process*>();
1768  if (nrn_is_artificial_[i] == 0) {
1769  int inode = ml->nodelist[j]->v_node_index;
1770  pp->nvi_ = d.lcv_ + cellnum[inode];
1771  } else {
1772  pp->nvi_ = nullptr;
1773  }
1774  }
1775  }
1776  }
1777  }
1778  }
1779  return true;
1780 }
1781 
1782 void NetCvode::fill_global_ba(NrnThread* nt, int bat, BAMechList** baml) {
1783  NrnThreadBAList* tbl;
1784  for (tbl = nt->tbl[bat]; tbl; tbl = tbl->next) {
1785  BAMechList* ba = new BAMechList(baml);
1786  ba->bam = tbl->bam;
1787  ba->ml.push_back(tbl->ml);
1788  }
1789 }
1790 
1791 void NetCvode::fill_local_ba(int* celnum, NetCvodeThreadData& d) {
1792  fill_local_ba_cnt(BEFORE_BREAKPOINT, celnum, d);
1793  fill_local_ba_cnt(AFTER_SOLVE, celnum, d);
1794  fill_local_ba_cnt(BEFORE_STEP, celnum, d);
1795 }
1796 
1797 void NetCvode::fill_local_ba_cnt(int bat, int* celnum, NetCvodeThreadData& d) {
1798  BAMech* bam;
1799  for (bam = bamech_[bat]; bam; bam = bam->next) {
1800  for (int icv = 0; icv < d.nlcv_; ++icv) {
1801  Cvode* cv = d.lcv_ + icv;
1802  assert(cv->nctd_ == 1);
1803  for (CvMembList* cml = cv->ctd_[0].cv_memb_list_; cml; cml = cml->next) {
1804  if (cml->index == bam->type) {
1805  BAMechList* bl = cvbml(bat, bam, cv);
1806  bl->bam = bam;
1807  for (auto& ml: cml->ml) {
1808  bl->ml.push_back(&ml);
1809  }
1810  }
1811  }
1812  }
1813  }
1814 }
1815 
1816 BAMechList* NetCvode::cvbml(int bat, BAMech* bam, Cvode* cv) {
1817  BAMechList** pbml;
1818  BAMechList* ba;
1819  if (bat == BEFORE_BREAKPOINT) {
1820  pbml = &cv->ctd_->before_breakpoint_;
1821  } else if (bat == AFTER_SOLVE) {
1822  pbml = &cv->ctd_->after_solve_;
1823  } else {
1824  pbml = &cv->ctd_->before_step_;
1825  }
1826  if (!*pbml) {
1827  ba = new BAMechList(pbml);
1828  } else {
1829  for (ba = *pbml; ba; ba = ba->next) {
1830  if (ba->bam->type == bam->type) {
1831  return ba;
1832  }
1833  }
1834  ba = new BAMechList(pbml);
1835  }
1836  ba->bam = bam;
1837  return ba;
1838 }
1839 
1840 /*
1841 The path through NetCvode::solve path is determined by the case dimensions of
1842 (single step, integrate to tout) and (no model, global dt, localdt).
1843 For threads there is one more constraint--- do not allow t0_ to pass
1844 by the minimum interthread netcon delay integration interval barrier
1845 without making sure all the interthread events to be delivered before
1846 that barrier are on the thread queue. For classical mpi spike exchange
1847 this was ensured by a NetParEvent which provided a synchronization barrier.
1848 We generalized this to a NetParEvent per thread and a thread barrier but
1849 there was a consequent loss of the possibility of sequential threads since
1850 in that context a barrier makes no sense (each job must run to completion).
1851 Hence the desire to avoid barriers and handle the interval barrier explicity
1852 here to make sure NetCvode::enqueue is called frequently enough.
1853 (Actually, it is called very frequently since it is called by deliver_events,
1854 so it is only required that the interval between the least and greatest
1855 integrator t0_ be less than the maximum).
1856 
1857 Without a thread barrier in NetParEvent,
1858 this mostly affects the "integrate to tout" case. But it also affects
1859 the single step case in that we are not allowed to handle any
1860 events with delivery time > barrier time. Since a microstep does the
1861 earliest next thing, we need to check that before the call.
1862 
1863 Can we deal with multisplit conveniently without a thread barrier.
1864 Yes if we split up the process into its three phases of triangularization,
1865 reduced tree solve, back substitution. No if we retain a single
1866 integration step quantum for the thread.
1867 Without barriers, we end up with finer and finer grain nrn_multithread_job.
1868 
1869 It is sounding more and more reasonable to sacrifice the debugging convenience
1870 of sequential threads in favor of allowing thread barriers.
1871 ...but... a look at the nrn_fixed_step and nrn_multisplit_solve shows
1872 that it would certainly be easy to split into the proper
1873 nrn_multithread_job groups since it is already functionally decomposed
1874 in that way. And we may want to limit NetParEvent to serve only as
1875 interprocessor spike exchange signals for the main thread.
1876 ...but... a look at cvode in a multisplit context
1877 means there must be one global cvode instance
1878 and when f and jacob is called it would divide there and do the scatter
1879 gather etc. Of course, with separate cvode instances with multisplit we
1880 still have to have a proper Vector library which does the corresponding
1881 mpi reduce functions. Conceptually much simpler with barrier and maybe
1882 impossible without. If we went with one global cvode it would be
1883 possible. And cvode overhead seems independent of number of equations
1884 so confining it to the main thread may not be bad.
1885 
1886 The principle multithread domain we design for below is the few event,
1887 multisplit case. That is, there is one cvode instance managed by thread 0
1888 and all events go onto one queue. However, an event is delivered according
1889 to its proper delivery thread. Note that the possiblity of 0 delay
1890 events is allowed. There is nothing that can be done at the minimum
1891 delay integration interval level since each step divides into a dozen or so
1892 multithread jobs.
1893 
1894 Threads and lvardt.
1895 Consider the global cv (used to be p.lcv_[0]) as gcv_ which has ctd[nrn_nthread]
1896 instances of separate CvodeThreadData and works with multisplit.
1897 Now consider the lvardt method (used to be supported by p.lcv_[i]) as
1898 NetCvodeThreadData instances of lcv_[i] and of course move tq_ into
1899 the NetCvodeThreadData. Then each of the p.lcv_[i] would have Cvode.nctd_
1900 equal 1 in which p.lcv_[i].ctd_[0] is the proper CvodeThreadData. Then
1901 Cvode would never look at nrn_nthread to determine the CvodeThreadData
1902 but only the Cvode.nctd_. And if Cvode.nctd_ > 1 which would be
1903 possible only for gcv_, only then would nt->id be used to get the proper
1904 CvodeThreadData. We presume for now that if lvardt is used with nrn_nthread > 1
1905 then the usual minimum delay interval requirements hold for interthread
1906 events.
1907 
1908 Inter-Thread-Events (possibility of 0 delay).
1909 
1910 The fixed step method is that for each step, the sequence of actions
1911 for each thread is:
1912 1) at time tbegin: check thresholds, if source and target on same thread
1913  put directly onto queue. If different threads (PreSyn only), do an
1914  interthread send which puts the event into the target thread
1915  inter_thread_events list. Finally we deliver all events up to tbegin+.5dt,
1916  this first transfers all the threads inter-thread-events onto the queue.
1917 2) at time tbegin + .5dt: v(tbegin) -> v(tend)
1918 3) at time tend: integrate states one step using v(tend)
1919 4) deliver events up to but not past tend (first transfers inter-thread-events
1920  onto queue).
1921 Therefore, a zero-delay inter-thread-event from an artificial cell
1922 generated in step 4 may or may not be delivered
1923 in the time step it is generated. And zero-delay threshold detection interthread
1924 events will be delivered in the time step but either in step 1 or step 4 (ie.
1925 beginning or end of the time step). For this reason, if there are zero-delay
1926 NetCon, then both the source and target should be on the same thread. In practice
1927 we should force them onto thread 0 or at least the source onto the
1928 target thread.
1929 
1930 What about cvode?
1931 Global variable time step method.
1932 As mentioned above, all events, when global cvode active, go onto the thread 0 event
1933 queue (interthread via the thread 0 inter_thread_events list)
1934 and from there are delivered in the context of the proper thread
1935 for cache efficiency (by means of nrn_onethread_job.) Again, as mentioned,
1936 the design side is for few events. With this in mind, there does not seem
1937 any impediment to 0 delay events. But note that an event with source and
1938 target on thread 2 (e.g. a self event) goes onto the thread 0 inter_thread_events
1939 list (in the context of thread 2), then in the context of thread 0 is transferred
1940 from the thread 0 inter_thread_events list to the thread 0 queue, then
1941 in the context of thread 0, the event is taken off the queue and delivered
1942 in the context of thread 2 (by means of nrn_onethread_job). (See why we
1943 are thinking few events? A bothersome aspect is that after every event
1944 delivery least_t has to enqueue onto the thread 0 queue the nthread
1945 inter_thread_events lists.
1946 The one queue idea for global variable time step is unsound because of the
1947 problem that multiple threads call the queue methods and so cause excessive
1948 cache line sharing. And if we avoided this through the use of the
1949 inter_thread_events list then consider a 0 delay NetCon
1950 event between artificial cells on thread 2 and thread 3.
1951 thread 0 in deliver_events_when_threads, least event for thread 2
1952 thread 2 (NET_RECEIVE -> net_send -> PreSyn::send -> p[3].interthead_send
1953 thread 0 enqueue onto thread 0 queue all inter_thread_events lists
1954 thread 0 least event for thread 3
1955 thread 3 (NET_RECEIVE ...)
1956 Actually, there are real problems. E.g ConditionEvent::condition is
1957 in the context of some thread and must remove an event on the thread 0 queue.
1958 That is a recipe for horrendous cacheline sharing and is the whole reason
1959 we designed inter_thread_events in the first place. Also the call to
1960 enqueue_thread0() is multiplying alarmingly (every call before least_t())
1961 and the reason for the privileged thread 0 queue has more or less disappeared.
1962 Instead we only need an effective reduce to find the minimum of the least_t()
1963 in each thread. Expensive but no more expensive than the single queue and without
1964 the cache-line shareing. And allows 0 delay events. And keeps a kind of uniformity
1965 between fixed step, global cvode, and the future lvardt in that each thread
1966 has its own event queue.
1967 Far reaching Local variable time step method change.
1968 gcv_ if it exists, refers to the global variable time step method
1969 and there are nthread CvodeThreadData instances in ctd_. If gcv_ is 0 and
1970 !empty_, then each NetCvodeThreadData manages an array of nlcv_
1971 Cvode instances in the lcv_ array. Each Cvode instance has only one ctd_
1972 Thus for global step the CvodeThreadData for a thread is gcv_->ctd_[i] whereas
1973 for lvardt it is p[i].lcv_[jcell_in_thread_i].ctd_[0].
1974 */
1975 
1976 int NetCvode::solve(double tout) {
1977  if (nrn_nthread > 1) {
1978  return solve_when_threads(tout); // more or less a copy of below
1979  }
1980  NrnThread* nt = nrn_threads;
1981  int err = NVI_SUCCESS;
1982  if (empty_) {
1983  if (tout >= 0.) {
1984  while (p[0].tqe_->least_t() <= tout && stoprun == 0) {
1985  deliver_least_event(nt);
1986  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
1987  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
1988  }
1989  }
1990  if (stoprun == 0) {
1991  nt_t = tout;
1992  }
1993  } else {
1994  if (p[0].tqe_->least()) {
1995  nt_t = p[0].tqe_->least_t();
1996  deliver_events(p[0].tqe_->least_t(), nt);
1997  } else {
1998  nt_t += 1e6;
1999  }
2000  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
2001  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
2002  }
2003  }
2004  } else if (single_) {
2005  if (tout >= 0.) {
2006  while (gcv_->t_ < tout || p[0].tqe_->least_t() < tout) {
2007  err = global_microstep();
2008  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
2009  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
2010  }
2011  if (err != NVI_SUCCESS || stoprun) {
2012  return err;
2013  }
2014  }
2015  retreat(tout, gcv_);
2016  gcv_->record_continuous();
2017  } else {
2018  // advance or initialized
2019  double tc = gcv_->t_;
2020  initialized_ = false;
2021  while (gcv_->t_ <= tc && !initialized_) {
2022  err = global_microstep();
2023  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
2024  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
2025  }
2026  if (err != NVI_SUCCESS || stoprun) {
2027  return err;
2028  }
2029  }
2030  }
2031  } else if (!gcv_) { // lvardt
2032  auto const cache_token = nrn_ensure_model_data_are_sorted();
2033  if (tout >= 0.) {
2034  time_t rt = time(nullptr);
2035  // int cnt = 0;
2036  TQueue* tq = p[0].tq_;
2037  TQueue* tqe = p[0].tqe_;
2038  NrnThread* nt = nrn_threads;
2039  while (tq->least_t() < tout || tqe->least_t() <= tout) {
2040  err = local_microstep(cache_token, *nt);
2041  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
2042  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
2043  }
2044  if (err != NVI_SUCCESS || stoprun) {
2045  return err;
2046  }
2047 #if HAVE_IV
2048  IFGUI
2049  if (rt < time(nullptr)) {
2050  // if (++cnt > 10000) {
2051  // cnt = 0;
2052  Oc oc;
2053  oc.notify();
2054  single_event_run();
2055  rt = time(nullptr);
2056  }
2057  ENDGUI
2058 #endif
2059  }
2060  int n = p[0].nlcv_;
2061  Cvode* lcv = p[0].lcv_;
2062  for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
2063  local_retreat(tout, lcv + i);
2064  lcv[i].record_continuous();
2065  }
2066  } else {
2067  // an fadvance is not every microstep but
2068  // only when all the discontinuities at te take place or
2069  // tc increases.
2070  TQueue* tq = p[0].tq_;
2071  double tc = tq->least_t();
2072  double te = p[0].tqe_->least_t();
2073  while (tq->least_t() <= tc && p[0].tqe_->least_t() <= te) {
2074  err = local_microstep(cache_token, *nrn_threads);
2075  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
2076  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
2077  }
2078  if (err != NVI_SUCCESS || stoprun) {
2079  return err;
2080  }
2081  }
2082  // But make sure t is not past the least time.
2083  // fadvance and local step do not coexist seamlessly.
2084  nt_t = tq->least_t();
2085  if (te < nt_t) {
2086  nt_t = te;
2087  }
2088  }
2089  } else {
2090  nt_t += 1e9;
2091  }
2092  return err;
2093 }
2094 
2095 void NetCvode::deliver_least_event(NrnThread* nt) {
2096  TQItem* q = p[nt->id].tqe_->least();
2097  DiscreteEvent* de = (DiscreteEvent*) q->data_;
2098  double tt = q->t_;
2099  p[nt->id].tqe_->remove(q);
2100 #if PRINT_EVENT
2101  if (print_event_) {
2102  de->pr("deliver", tt, this);
2103  }
2104 #endif
2105  STATISTICS(deliver_cnt_);
2106  de->deliver(tt, this, nt);
2107 }
2108 
2109 bool NetCvode::deliver_event(double til, NrnThread* nt) {
2110  TQItem* q;
2111  if ((q = p[nt->id].tqe_->atomic_dq(til)) != 0) {
2112  DiscreteEvent* de = (DiscreteEvent*) q->data_;
2113  double tt = q->t_;
2114  p[nt->id].tqe_->release(q);
2115 #if PRINT_EVENT
2116  if (print_event_) {
2117  de->pr("deliver", tt, this);
2118  }
2119 #endif
2120  STATISTICS(deliver_cnt_);
2121  de->deliver(tt, this, nt);
2122  return true;
2123  } else {
2124  return false;
2125  }
2126 }
2127 
2128 int NetCvode::local_microstep(neuron::model_sorted_token const& sorted_token, NrnThread& ntr) {
2129  auto* const nt = &ntr;
2130  int err = NVI_SUCCESS;
2131  int i = nt->id;
2132  if (p[i].tqe_->least_t() <= p[i].tq_->least_t()) {
2133  deliver_least_event(nt);
2134  } else {
2135  TQItem* q = p[i].tq_->least();
2136  Cvode* cv = (Cvode*) q->data_;
2137  err = cv->handle_step(sorted_token, this, 1e100);
2138  p[i].tq_->move_least(cv->t_);
2139  }
2140  return err;
2141 }
2142 
2143 int NetCvode::global_microstep() {
2144  NrnThread* nt = nrn_threads;
2145  int err = NVI_SUCCESS;
2146  double tt = p[0].tqe_->least_t();
2147  double tdiff = tt - gcv_->t_;
2148  if (tdiff <= 0) {
2149  // since events do not internally retreat with the
2150  // global step, we should already be at the event time
2151  // if this is too strict, we could use eps(list_->t_).
2152  assert(tdiff == 0.0 || (gcv_->tstop_begin_ <= tt && tt <= gcv_->tstop_end_));
2153  deliver_events(tt, nt);
2154  } else {
2155  err = gcv_->handle_step(nrn_ensure_model_data_are_sorted(), this, tt);
2156  }
2157  if (p[0].tqe_->least_t() < gcv_->t_) {
2158  gcv_->interpolate(p[0].tqe_->least_t());
2159  }
2160  return err;
2161 }
2162 
2163 int Cvode::handle_step(neuron::model_sorted_token const& sorted_token, NetCvode* ns, double te) {
2164  int err = NVI_SUCCESS;
2165  // first order correct condition evaluation goes here
2166  if (ns->condition_order() == 1) {
2167  if (ns->gcv_) { // global step
2168  for (int i = 0; i < nctd_; ++i) {
2169  nrn_threads[i]._t = t_; // for global step could be assert
2170  }
2171  check_deliver();
2172  // done if the check puts a 0 delay event on queue
2173  if (nctd_ > 1) {
2174  int tid;
2175  if (ns->allthread_least_t(tid) <= t_) {
2176  return err;
2177  }
2178  } else {
2179  if (ns->p[0].tqe_->least_t() <= t_) {
2180  return err;
2181  }
2182  }
2183  } else { // lvardt so in a specific thread
2184  // for localstep method t is for a different cvode.fun call
2185  nth_->_t = t_;
2186  check_deliver(nth_);
2187  if (ns->p[nth_->id].tqe_->least_t() <= t_) {
2188  return err;
2189  }
2190  }
2191  }
2192  if (initialize_) {
2193  err = init(t_);
2194  if (ns->gcv_) {
2195  ns->initialized_ = true;
2196  }
2197  // second order correct condition evaluation goes here
2198  if (ns->condition_order() == 2) {
2199  evaluate_conditions(nth_);
2200  }
2201  } else if (te <= tn_) {
2202  err = interpolate(te);
2203  } else if (t_ < tn_) {
2204  err = interpolate(tn_);
2205  } else {
2206  record_continuous();
2207  err = advance_tn(sorted_token);
2208  // second order correct condition evaluation goes here
2209  if (ns->condition_order() == 2) {
2210  evaluate_conditions(nth_);
2211  }
2212  }
2213  return err;
2214 }

2319  }

2321  q = net_cvode_instance->event(td, se, nt);
2322 #endif

2325  }

2329 void artcell_net_send(Datum* v, double* weight, Point_process* pnt, double td, double flag) {
2330  if (nrn_use_selfqueue_ && flag == 1.0) {
2331  STATISTICS(SelfEvent::selfevent_send_);
2332  NrnThread* nt = PP2NT(pnt);
2333  NetCvodeThreadData& p = net_cvode_instance->p[nt->id];
2334  SelfEvent* se = p.sepool_->alloc();
2335  se->flag_ = flag;
2336  se->target_ = pnt;
2337  se->weight_ = weight;
2338  se->movable_ = v; // needed for SaveState
2339  assert(net_cvode_instance);
2340  ++p.unreffed_event_cnt_;
2341  if (td < nt->_t) {
2342  char buf[100];
2343  Sprintf(buf, "net_send td-t = %g", td - nt->_t);
2344  se->pr(buf, td, net_cvode_instance);
2345  hoc_execerror("net_send delay < 0", 0);
2346  }
2347  TQItem* q = p.selfqueue_->insert(se);
2348  q->t_ = td;
2349  *v = q;
2350  // printf("artcell_net_send %g %s %g %p\n", td, hoc_object_name(pnt->ob), flag, v);
2351  if (q->t_ < p.immediate_deliver_) {
2352  // printf("artcell_net_send_ %s immediate %g %g %g\n", hoc_object_name(pnt->ob),
2353  // nt->_t, q->t_, p.immediate_deliver_);
2354  SelfEvent* se = (SelfEvent*) q->data_;
2355  p.selfqueue_->remove(q);
2356  se->deliver(td, net_cvode_instance, nt);
2357  }
2358  } else {
2359  nrn_net_send(v, weight, pnt, td, flag);
2360  }
2361 }

2393 
2394 void _nrn_watch_activate(Datum* d,
2395  double (*c)(Point_process*),
2396  int i,
2397  Point_process* pnt,
2398  int r,
2399  double flag) {
2400  auto* wl = d->get<WatchList*>();
2401  auto* wc = d[i].get<WatchCondition*>();
2402  if (!wl || !wc) {
2403  // When c is NULL, i.e. called from CoreNEURON,
2404  // we never get here because we made sure
2405  // _nrn_watch_allocated for this has been called earlier from
2406  // within the translated mod file.
2407  _nrn_watch_allocate(d, c, i, pnt, flag);
2408  // d[0] and d[i] have now been updated
2409  wl = d->get<WatchList*>();
2410  wc = d[i].get<WatchCondition*>();
2411  }
2412  if (r == 0) {
2413  for (auto wc1: *wl) {
2414  wc1->Remove();
2415  if (wc1->qthresh_) { // is it on the queue?
2416  net_cvode_instance->remove_event(wc1->qthresh_, PP2NT(pnt)->id);
2417  wc1->qthresh_ = nullptr;
2418  }
2419  }
2420  wl->clear();
2421  }
2422  wl->push_back(wc);
2423  wc->activate(flag); // nr_flag_ (NetReceive flag) not flag_ for above threshold.
2424 }
2425 
2426 /*
2427 An example of a call to _nrn_watch_activate from within the NET_RECEIVE
2428 block of a translated mod file is
2429 _nrn_watch_activate(_watch_array, _watch1_cond, 1, _pnt, _watch_rm++, 2.0);
2430 
2431 _watch_array begins at _ppvar+first_index_of_watch_information and the number
2432  of indices is 1 more than the number of watch statements. Each of those
2433  (starting at index 1) is a pointer to a WatchCondition.
2434  The 0th is a pointer to a HTList (HeadTailList) of the active WatchConditions.
2435  Third arg is index of the WatchCondition to be activated.
2436  The _watch_rm when 0 means, empty the HTList before adding the
2437  WatchCondition to the HTList, when > 0, just add (It is possible for
2438  several WatchCondition to be active at the same time. That is useful when
2439  the conceptual condition is for a variable to be within a specific range
2440  or when multiple variables need to be watched at the same time.
2441  The last arg is the flag value used by the NET_RECEIVE block to activate
2442  a new set of WATCH statements. Note that that particular flag does not
2443  have to result in the activation of a new set. In that case, the old set
2444  stays active.
2445 
2446 Note. At time of writing this note,
2447  _watch_array[1:] are only created the first time that 'i' WatchCondition
2448  is activated. And at that time the 2nd callback arg is stored in the
2449  WatchCondition. So, at the moment, return from CoreNEURON cannot count on
2450  all WatchConditions being in existence. Given that the 2nd callback arg
2451  is only known to the translated mod file, the most straightforward solution
2452  is for nocmodl to generate
2453  an "initialization" function that calls all possible _nrn_watch_activate.
2454  That could be done at the Point_process* pnt creation time (or after
2455  transfer of WATCH info to CoreNEURON (using structure_change_cnt_).)
2456  It could even be done as necessary when CoreNEURON sends back activated
2457  WatchCondition info when the WatchCondition* slot on the NEURON side
2458  is NULL. Then the "initialization" function could call a stripped down
2459  version of _nrn_watch_activate for only its NULL slots.
2460 
2461 Here are some more notes about WatchCondition, HTList, HTListList, and
2462  WatchList.
2463  The (WatchList*)d->_pvoid is used only in _nrn_watch_activate to
2464  iterate over its previously activated list in order to remove all those from
2465  its HTList.
2466  WatchCondition is a subclass of ConditionEvent and HTList
2467  Because of the latter, we can say
2468  WatchCondition.Remove() and HTList.append(WatchCondition)
2469  The former can be called any number of times. When it is called it becomes
2470  a singleton WatchCondition (only in itself as an HTList).
2471  The latter can be called any number of times. Whereever the
2472  WatchCondition is located before calling HTList.append ---
2473  singleton, in another list, or already in this list --- it will end up
2474  as the htlist.Last()
2475 
2476 */
2477 
2478 /** Introduced so corenrn->nrn can request the mod file to make sure
2479  * all WatchCondition are allocated. When that is the case then
2480  * corenrn can call _nrn_watch_activate with all args filled out
2481  * because the allocated WatchCondition has double (*c_)(Point_process)
2482  * and flag_ filled in.
2483  **/
2484 void _nrn_watch_allocate(Datum* d,
2485  double (*c)(Point_process*),
2486  int i,
2487  Point_process* pnt,
2488  double flag) {
2489  if (!d->get<WatchList*>()) {
2490  *d = new WatchList;
2491  }
2492  if (!d[i].get<WatchCondition*>()) {
2493  WatchCondition* wc = new WatchCondition(pnt, c);
2494  wc->c_ = c;
2495  wc->nrflag_ = flag;
2496  d[i] = wc;
2497  // Simplify transfer to CoreNEURON
2498  // To avoid searching for the beginning of _watch_array after
2499  // transfer to CoreNEURON, compute the offset with respect to
2500  // dparam. That, of course, assumes NEURON and CoreNEURON
2501  // have same pdata arrangement.
2502  wc->watch_index_ = i + (d - pnt->prop->dparam);
2503  }
2504 }
2505 
2506 /** Watch info corenrn->nrn transfer requires all activated
2507  * WatchCondition be deactivated prior to mirroring the activation
2508  * that exists on the corenrn side.
2509  **/
2510 void nrn_watch_clear() {
2511  assert(net_cvode_instance->wl_list_.size() == (size_t) nrn_nthread);
2512  for (auto& htlists_of_thread: net_cvode_instance->wl_list_) {
2513  for (HTList* wl: htlists_of_thread) {
2514  wl->RemoveAll();
2515  }
2516  }
2517  // not necessary to empty the WatchList in the Point_process dparam array
2518  // as that will happen when _nrn_watch_activate is called with an r
2519  // arg of 0.
2520 }
2521 
2522 /** Called by Point_process destructor in translated mod file **/
2523 void _nrn_free_watch(Datum* d, int offset, int n) {
2524  int i;
2525  int nn = offset + n;
2526  if (auto* d_offset = d[offset].get<WatchList*>(); d_offset) {
2527  delete d_offset;
2528  d[offset] = nullptr;
2529  }
2530  for (i = offset + 1; i < nn; ++i) {
2531  if (auto* wc = d[i].get<WatchCondition*>(); wc) {
2532  wc->Remove();
2533  delete wc;
2534  d[i] = nullptr;
2535  }
2536  }
2537 }

2608 void NetCvode::hoc_event(double tt, const char* stmt, Object* ppobj, int reinit, Object* pyact) {
2609  if (!ppobj && tt - nt_t < 0) {
2610  return;
2611  }
2612 #if USENEOSIM
2613  if (neosim_entity_) {
2614  // ignore for neosim. There is no appropriate cvode_instance
2615  // cvode_instance->neosim_self_events_->insert(nt_t + delay, null_event_);
2616  } else
2617 #endif
2618  {
2619  NrnThread* nt = nrn_threads;
2620  if (nrn_nthread > 1 && (!cvode_active_ || localstep())) {
2621  if (ppobj) {
2622  int i = PP2NT(ob2pntproc(ppobj))->id;
2623  p[i].interthread_send(tt, HocEvent::alloc(stmt, ppobj, reinit, pyact), nt + i);
2624  nrn_interthread_enqueue(nt + i);
2625  } else {
2626  HocEvent* he = HocEvent::alloc(stmt, nullptr, 0, pyact);
2627  // put on each queue. The first thread to execute the deliver
2628  // for he will set the nrn_allthread_handle
2629  // callback which will cause all threads to rejoin at the
2630  // end of the current fixed step or, for var step methods,
2631  // after all events at this time are delivered. It is up
2632  // to the callers of the multithread_job functions
2633  // to do the right thing.
2634  for (int i = 0; i < nrn_nthread; ++i) {
2635  p[i].interthread_send(tt, he, nt + i);
2636  }
2637  nrn_multithread_job(nrn_interthread_enqueue);
2638  }
2639  } else {
2640  event(tt, HocEvent::alloc(stmt, ppobj, reinit, pyact), nt);
2641  }
2642  }
2643 }
2644 
2645 void NetCvode::allthread_handle() {
2646  nrn_allthread_handle = nullptr;
2647  t = nt_t;
2648  while (!allthread_hocevents_->empty()) {
2649  HocEvent* he = (*allthread_hocevents_)[0];
2650  allthread_hocevents_->erase(allthread_hocevents_->begin());
2651  he->allthread_handle();
2652  }
2653 }
2654 
2655 void NetCvode::allthread_handle(double tt, HocEvent* he, NrnThread* nt) {
2656  // printf("allthread_handle tt=%g nt=%d nt_t=%g\n", tt, nt->id, nt->_t);
2657  nt->_stop_stepping = 1;
2658  if (is_local()) {
2659  int i, n = p[nt->id].nlcv_;
2660  Cvode* lcv = p[nt->id].lcv_;
2661  if (n)
2662  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
2663  local_retreat(tt, lcv + i);
2664  if (!he->stmt()) {
2665  lcv[i].record_continuous();
2666  }
2667  }
2668  else {
2669  nt->_t = tt;
2670  }
2671  } else if (!he->stmt() && cvode_active_ && gcv_) {
2672  assert(MyMath::eq2(tt, gcv_->t_, NetCvode::eps(tt)));
2673  gcv_->record_continuous();
2674  }
2675  if (nt->id == 0) {
2676  nrn_allthread_handle = allthread_handle_callback;
2677  allthread_hocevents_->push_back(he);
2678  nt->_t = tt;
2679  }
2680  if (cvode_active_ && gcv_ && nrnmpi_numprocs > 1) {
2681  assert(nrn_nthread == 1);
2682  return;
2683  }
2684  // deliver any other events at this time (in particular, a possible NetParEvent)
2685  // to guarantee consistency of the NetParEvent for all threads
2686  // Otherwise, if some threads do a NetParEvent and others not, then
2687  // the interthread enqueue can put an earlier event onto the thread queue
2688  // than the last delivered event
2689  deliver_events(tt, nt);
2690 }

2707 void NetCvode::point_receive(int type, Point_process* pp, double* w, double f) {
2708  // this is the master thread. need to execute the thread associated
2709  // with the pp.

2711  if (id == 0) { // execute on this, the master thread
2712  (*pnt_receive[type])(pp, w, f);
2713  }else{
2714  // marshall the args
2715  PPArgs* p = ppargs + id;
2716  p->_type = type;
2717  p->pp = pp;
2718  p->w = w;
2719  p->f = f;
2720  nrn_onethread_job(id, point_receive_job);
2721  }
2722  // global queue with different threads putting things in
2723  // means no guarantee that something goes into the queue
2724  // to be delivered earlier than something last extracted.
2725  // so return to calling main thread only after the
2726  // worker thread is done. Too bad...
2727  // this needs to be worked on. Only thread id is executing.
2728  nrn_wait_for_threads();
2729 }

2732 void NetCvode::clear_events() {
2733  int i;
2734  deliver_cnt_ = net_event_cnt_ = 0;
2735  NetCon::netcon_send_active_ = 0;
2736  NetCon::netcon_send_inactive_ = 0;
2737  NetCon::netcon_deliver_ = 0;
2738  ConditionEvent::init_above_ = 0;
2739  ConditionEvent::send_qthresh_ = 0;
2740  ConditionEvent::deliver_qthresh_ = 0;
2741  ConditionEvent::abandon_ = 0;
2742  ConditionEvent::eq_abandon_ = 0;
2743  ConditionEvent::abandon_init_above_ = 0;
2744  ConditionEvent::abandon_init_below_ = 0;
2745  ConditionEvent::abandon_above_ = 0;
2746  ConditionEvent::abandon_below_ = 0;
2747  PreSyn::presyn_send_mindelay_ = 0;
2748  PreSyn::presyn_send_direct_ = 0;
2749  PreSyn::presyn_deliver_netcon_ = 0;
2750  PreSyn::presyn_deliver_direct_ = 0;
2751  PreSyn::presyn_deliver_ncsend_ = 0;
2752  SelfEvent::selfevent_send_ = 0;
2753  SelfEvent::selfevent_move_ = 0;
2754  SelfEvent::selfevent_deliver_ = 0;
2755  WatchCondition::watch_send_ = 0;
2756  WatchCondition::watch_deliver_ = 0;
2757  PlayRecordEvent::playrecord_deliver_ = 0;
2758  PlayRecordEvent::playrecord_send_ = 0;
2759  HocEvent::hocevent_send_ = 0;
2760  HocEvent::hocevent_deliver_ = 0;
2761  DiscreteEvent::discretevent_send_ = 0;
2762  DiscreteEvent::discretevent_deliver_ = 0;
2763  KSSingle::singleevent_deliver_ = 0;
2764  KSSingle::singleevent_move_ = 0;
2765 
2766  // SelfEvents need to be "freed". Other kinds of DiscreteEvents may
2767  // already have gone out of existence so the tqe_ may contain many
2768  // invalid item data pointers
2769  HocEvent::reclaim();
2770  allthread_hocevents_->clear();
2771  nrn_allthread_handle = nullptr;
2772 #if USENEOSIM
2773  if (p_nrn2neosim_send)
2774  for (i = 0; i < nlist_; ++i) {
2775  TQueue* tq = p.lcv_[i].neosim_self_events_;
2776  while (tq->least()) {
2777  tq->remove(tq->least());
2778  }
2779  // and have already been reclaimed by SelfEvent::reclaim()
2780  }
2781 #endif
2782  if (!MUTCONSTRUCTED) {
2783  MUTCONSTRUCT(1);
2784  }
2785  enqueueing_ = 0;
2786  for (i = 0; i < nrn_nthread; ++i) {
2787  NetCvodeThreadData& d = p[i];
2788  delete std::exchange(d.tqe_, new TQueue(p[i].tpool_));
2789  d.unreffed_event_cnt_ = 0;
2790  if (d.sepool_) {
2791  d.sepool_->free_all();
2792  }
2793  d.immediate_deliver_ = -1e100;
2794  d.ite_cnt_ = 0;
2795  if (nrn_use_selfqueue_) {
2796  if (!d.selfqueue_) {
2797  d.selfqueue_ = new SelfQueue(d.tpool_, 0);
2798  } else {
2799  d.selfqueue_->remove_all();
2800  }
2801  }
2802  d.tqe_->nshift_ = -1;
2803  d.tqe_->shift_bin(nt_t - 0.5 * nt_dt);
2804  }
2805  // I don't believe this is needed anymore since cvode not needed
2806  // til delivery.
2807  if (cvode_active_) { // in case there is a net_send from INITIAL cvode
2808  // then this needs to be done before INITIAL blocks are called
2809  init_global();
2810  }
2811 }

2813 // Frees the allocated memory for the SelfEvent pool and TQItemPool after cleaning them
2814 void NetCvode::free_event_pools() {
2815  clear_events();
2816  for (int i = 0; i < nrn_nthread; ++i) {
2817  NetCvodeThreadData& d = p[i];
2818  delete std::exchange(d.sepool_, nullptr);
2819  delete std::exchange(d.selfqueue_, nullptr);
2820  delete std::exchange(d.tqe_, nullptr);
2821  if (d.tpool_) {
2822  d.tpool_->free_all();
2823  delete std::exchange(d.tpool_, nullptr);
2824  }
2825  }
2826 }
2827 
2828 void NetCvode::init_events() {
2829  hoc_Item* q;
2830  int i, j;
2831  for (i = 0; i < nrn_nthread; ++i) {
2832  p[i].tqe_->nshift_ = -1;
2833  // first bin starts 1/2 time step early because per time step
2834  // binq delivery during simulation from deliver_net_events,
2835  // after delivering all events in the current bin, shifts to
2836  // nt->_t + 0.5*nt->_dt where nt->_t is a multiple of dt.
2837  p[i].tqe_->shift_bin(nt_t - 0.5 * nt_dt);
2838  }
2839  if (psl_) {
2840  ITERATE(q, psl_) {
2841  PreSyn* ps = (PreSyn*) VOIDITM(q);
2842  ps->init();
2843  ps->flag_ = false;
2844  NetConPList& dil = ps->dil_;
2845  ps->use_min_delay_ = 0;
2846 #if USE_MIN_DELAY
2847  // also decide what to do about use_min_delay_
2848  // the rule for now is to use it if all delays are
2849  // the same and there are more than 2
2850  {
2851  if (dil.size() > 2) {
2852  ps->use_min_delay_ = 1;
2853  ps->delay_ = dil[0]->delay_;
2854  }
2855  }
2856 #endif // USE_MIN_DELAY
2857 
2858  for (const auto& d: dil) {
2859  if (ps->use_min_delay_ && ps->delay_ != d->delay_) {
2860  ps->use_min_delay_ = false;
2861  }
2862  }
2863  }
2864  }
2865  // iterate over all NetCon in creation order to call
2866  // NETRECEIVE INITIAL blocks.
2867  static hoc_List* nclist = NULL;
2868  if (!nclist) {
2869  Symbol* sym = hoc_lookup("NetCon");
2870  nclist = sym->u.ctemplate->olist;
2871  }
2872  ITERATE(q, nclist) {
2873  Object* obj = OBJ(q);
2874  auto* d = static_cast<NetCon*>(obj->u.this_pointer);
2875  if (d->target_) {
2876  int type = d->target_->prop->_type; // somehow prop is non-deterministically-null here
2877  if (pnt_receive_init[type]) {
2878  (*pnt_receive_init[type])(d->target_, d->weight_, 0);
2879  } else {
2880  // not the first
2881  for (j = d->cnt_ - 1; j > 0; --j) {
2882  d->weight_[j] = 0.;
2883  }
2884  }
2885  }
2886  }
2887  if (gcv_) {
2888  for (int j = 0; j < nrn_nthread; ++j) {
2889  if (gcv_->ctd_[j].watch_list_) {
2890  gcv_->ctd_[j].watch_list_->RemoveAll();
2891  }
2892  }
2893  } else {
2894  for (int j = 0; j < nrn_nthread; ++j) {
2895  NetCvodeThreadData& d = p[j];
2896  for (i = 0; i < d.nlcv_; ++i) {
2897  if (d.lcv_[i].ctd_[0].watch_list_) {
2898  d.lcv_[i].ctd_[0].watch_list_->RemoveAll();
2899  }
2900  }
2901  }
2902  }
2903 }
2904 
2905 double PreSyn::mindelay() {
2906  double md = 1e9;
2907  for (const auto& d: dil_) {
2908  if (md > d->delay_) {
2909  md = d->delay_;
2910  }
2911  }
2912  return md;
2913 }

2945 static int event_info_type_;
2946 static IvocVect* event_info_tvec_;
2947 static IvocVect* event_info_flagvec_;
2948 static OcList* event_info_list_; // netcon or point_process
2949 
2950 static void event_info_callback(const TQItem*, int);
2951 static void event_info_callback(const TQItem* q, int) {
2952  DiscreteEvent* d = (DiscreteEvent*) q->data_;
2953  switch (d->type()) {
2954  case NetConType:
2955  if (event_info_type_ == NetConType) {
2956  auto* nc = static_cast<NetCon*>(d);
2957  event_info_tvec_->push_back(q->t_);
2958  event_info_list_->append(nc->obj_);
2959  }
2960  break;
2961  case SelfEventType:
2962  if (event_info_type_ == SelfEventType) {
2963  auto* se = static_cast<SelfEvent*>(d);
2964  event_info_tvec_->push_back(q->t_);
2965  event_info_flagvec_->push_back(se->flag_);
2966  event_info_list_->append(se->target_->ob);
2967  }
2968  break;
2969  case PreSynType:
2970  if (event_info_type_ == NetConType) {
2971  auto* ps = static_cast<PreSyn*>(d);
2972  for (const auto& nc: reverse(ps->dil_)) {
2973  double td = nc->delay_ - ps->delay_;
2974  event_info_tvec_->push_back(q->t_ + td);
2975  event_info_list_->append(nc->obj_);
2976  }
2977  }
2978  break;
2979  }
2980 }

2982 void NetCvode::event_queue_info() {
2983  // dangerous since many events can go out of existence after
2984  // a simulation and before NetCvode::clear at the next initialization
2985  int i = 1;
2986  event_info_type_ = (int) chkarg(i++, 2, 3);
2987  event_info_tvec_ = vector_arg(i++);
2988  event_info_tvec_->resize(0);
2989  if (event_info_type_ == SelfEventType) {
2990  event_info_flagvec_ = vector_arg(i++);
2991  event_info_flagvec_->resize(0);
2992  }
2993  Object* o = *hoc_objgetarg(i++);
2994  check_obj_type(o, "List");
2995  event_info_list_ = (OcList*) o->u.this_pointer;
2996  event_info_list_->remove_all();
2997  p[0].tqe_->forall_callback(event_info_callback);
2998 }

3031 void NetCon::deliver(double tt, NetCvode* ns, NrnThread* nt) {
3032  assert(target_);
3033  int type = target_->prop->_type;
3034  std::string ss("net-receive-");
3035  ss += memb_func[type].sym->name;
3036  nrn::Instrumentor::phase p_get_pnt_receive(ss.c_str());
3037  if (PP2NT(target_) != nt) {
3038  Printf("NetCon::deliver nt=%d target=%d\n", nt->id, PP2NT(target_)->id);
3039  }
3040  assert(PP2NT(target_) == nt);
3041  Cvode* cv = (Cvode*) target_->nvi_;
3042  if (nrn_use_selfqueue_ && nrn_is_artificial_[type]) {
3043  auto& datum = target_->prop->dparam[nrn_artcell_qindex_[type]];
3044  TQItem* q;
3045  while ((q = datum.get<TQItem*>()) && q->t_ < tt) {
3046  double t1 = q->t_;
3047  auto* const se = static_cast<SelfEvent*>(ns->p[nt->id].selfqueue_->remove(q));
3048  // printf("%d NetCon::deliver %g , earlier selfevent at %g\n", nrnmpi_myid, tt, q->t_);
3049  se->deliver(t1, ns, nt);
3050  }
3051  }
3052  if (cvode_active_ && cv) {
3053  ns->local_retreat(tt, cv);
3054  cv->set_init_flag();
3055  } else {
3056  // no interpolation necessary for local step method and ARTIFICIAL_CELL
3057  nt->_t = tt;
3058  }
3059 
3060  // printf("NetCon::deliver t=%g tt=%g %s\n", t, tt, hoc_object_name(target_->ob));
3061  STATISTICS(netcon_deliver_);
3062  POINT_RECEIVE(type, target_, weight_, 0);
3063  if (errno) {
3064  if (nrn_errno_check(type)) {
3065  hoc_warning("errno set during NetCon deliver to NET_RECEIVE", (char*) 0);
3066  }
3067  }
3068 }

3072 }

3096 void PreSyn::send(double tt, NetCvode* ns, NrnThread* nt) {
3097  int i;
3098  record(tt);
3099 #ifndef USENCS
3100  if (use_min_delay_) {
3101  STATISTICS(presyn_send_mindelay_);
3102  for (i = 0; i < nrn_nthread; ++i) {
3103  if (nt->id == i) {
3104  ns->bin_event(tt + delay_, this, nt);
3105  } else {
3106  ns->p[i].interthread_send(tt + delay_, this, nrn_threads + i);
3107  }
3108  }
3109  } else {
3110  STATISTICS(presyn_send_direct_);
3111  for (const auto& d: dil_) {
3112  if (d->active_ && d->target_) {
3113  NrnThread* n = PP2NT(d->target_);
3114  if (nt == n) {
3115  ns->bin_event(tt + d->delay_, d, n);
3116  } else {
3117  ns->p[n->id].interthread_send(tt + d->delay_, d, n);
3118  }
3119  }
3120  }
3121  }
3122 #endif // ndef USENCS
3123 #if USENCS || NRNMPI
3124  if (output_index_ >= 0) {
3125 #if NRNMPI
3126  if (use_multisend_) {
3127  nrn_multisend_send(this, tt);
3128  } else {
3129  if (nrn_use_localgid_) {
3130  nrn_outputevent(localgid_, tt);
3131  } else
3132 #endif // NRNMPI
3133  nrn2ncs_outputevent(output_index_, tt);
3134 #if NRNMPI
3135  }
3136 #endif // NRNMPI
3137 #if NRN_MUSIC
3138  if (music_port_) {
3139  nrnmusic_injectlist(music_port_, tt);
3140  }
3141 #endif // NRN_MUSIC
3142  }
3143 #endif // USENCS || NRNMPI
3144 }

3146 void PreSyn::deliver(double tt, NetCvode* ns, NrnThread* nt) {
3147  if (qthresh_) {
3148  // the thread is the one that owns the PreSyn
3149  assert(nt == nt_);
3150  qthresh_ = nullptr;
3151  // printf("PreSyn::deliver %s condition event tt=%20.15g\n", ssrc_?secname(ssrc_):"", tt);
3152  STATISTICS(deliver_qthresh_);
3153  // If local variable time step and send is recorded,
3154  // tt will be recorded correctly. But if the recording results
3155  // in a callback, the user might inquire about other variables
3156  // as well, so perhaps we need to interpolate first.
3157  if (!ns->gcv_ && stmt_) {
3158  int i = nt->id;
3159  TQItem* q = ns->p[i].tq_->least();
3160  Cvode* cv = (Cvode*) q->data_;
3161  if (tt < cv->t_) {
3162  int err = NVI_SUCCESS;
3163  err = cv->handle_step(nrn_ensure_model_data_are_sorted(), ns, tt);
3164  ns->p[i].tq_->move_least(cv->t_);
3165  }
3166  }
3167  send(tt, ns, nt);
3168  return;
3169  }
3170  // the thread is the one that owns the targets
3171  STATISTICS(presyn_deliver_netcon_);
3172  for (const auto& d: dil_) {
3173  if (d->active_ && d->target_ && PP2NT(d->target_) == nt) {
3174  double dtt = d->delay_ - delay_;
3175  if (dtt == 0.) {
3176  STATISTICS(presyn_deliver_direct_);
3177  STATISTICS(deliver_cnt_);
3178  d->deliver(tt, ns, nt);
3179  } else if (dtt < 0.) {
3180  hoc_execerror("internal error: Source delay is > NetCon delay", 0);
3181  } else {
3182  STATISTICS(presyn_deliver_ncsend_);
3183  ns->event(tt + dtt, d, nt);
3184  }
3185  }
3186  }
3187 }
3188 
3189 // used by bbsavestate since during restore, some NetCon spikes may
3190 // have already been delivered while others need to be delivered in
3191 // the future. Not implemented fof qthresh_ case. No statistics.
3192 void PreSyn::fanout(double td, NetCvode* ns, NrnThread* nt) {
3193  for (const auto& d: dil_) {
3194  if (d->active_ && d->target_ && PP2NT(d->target_) == nt) {
3195  double dtt = d->delay_ - delay_;
3196  ns->bin_event(td + dtt, d, nt);
3197  }
3198  }
3199 }

3206  NrnThread* nt = 0;
3207  assert(0);
3208  if (qthresh_) {
3209  qthresh_ = nullptr;
3210  // printf("PreSyn::deliver %s condition event tt=%20.15g\n", ssrc_?secname(ssrc_):"", tt);
3211  STATISTICS(deliver_qthresh_);
3212  send(tt, ns, nt);
3213  return;
3214  }

3220  hoc_execerror("internal error: Source delay is > NetCon delay", 0);

3253 DiscreteEvent* SelfEvent::savestate_read(FILE* f) {
3254  SelfEvent* se = new SelfEvent();
3255  char buf[300];
3256  char ppname[200];
3257  int ppindex, ncindex, moff, pptype;
3258  double flag;
3259  nrn_assert(fgets(buf, 300, f));
3260  nrn_assert(
3261  sscanf(buf, "%s %d %d %d %d %lf\n", ppname, &ppindex, &pptype, &ncindex, &moff, &flag) ==
3262  6);
3263  se->target_ = SelfEvent::index2pp(pptype, ppindex);
3264  se->weight_ = nullptr;

3267  se->weight_ = nc->weight_;
3268  }

3271  return se;

3276 Point_process* SelfEvent::index2pp(int type, int oindex) {
3277  // code the type and object index together
3278  if (!sepp_) {
3279  int i;
3280  sepp_.reset(new SelfEventPPTable());
3281  sepp_->reserve(211);
3282  // should only be the ones that call net_send
3283  for (i = 0; i < n_memb_func; ++i)
3284  if (pnt_receive[i]) {
3285  hoc_List* hl = nrn_pnt_template_[i]->olist;
3286  hoc_Item* q;
3287  ITERATE(q, hl) {
3288  Object* o = OBJ(q);
3289  (*sepp_)[i + n_memb_func * o->index] = ob2pntproc(o);
3290  }
3291  }
3292  }
3293  const auto& iter = sepp_->find(type + n_memb_func * oindex);
3294  nrn_assert(iter != sepp_->end());
3295  return iter->second;
3296 }
