3323 void SelfEvent::deliver(double tt, NetCvode* ns, NrnThread* nt) {
3324  Cvode* cv = (Cvode*) target_->nvi_;
3325  int type = target_->prop->_type;
3326  assert(nt == PP2NT(target_));
3327  if (nrn_use_selfqueue_ && nrn_is_artificial_[type]) { // handle possible earlier flag=1 self
3328  // event
3329  if (flag_ == 1.0) {
3330  *movable_ = nullptr;
3331  }
3332  TQItem* q;
3333  while ((q = movable_->get<TQItem*>()) != 0 && q->t_ <= tt) {
3334  // printf("handle earlier %g selfqueue event from within %g SelfEvent::deliver\n",
3335  // q->t_, tt);
3336  double t1 = q->t_;
3337  SelfEvent* se = (SelfEvent*) ns->p[nt->id].selfqueue_->remove(q);
3338  PP2t(target_) = t1;
3339  se->call_net_receive(ns);
3340  }
3341  }
3342  if (cvode_active_ && cv) {
3343  ns->local_retreat(tt, cv);
3344  cv->set_init_flag();
3345  } else {
3346  PP2t(target_) = tt;
3347  }
3348  // printf("SelfEvent::deliver t=%g tt=%g %s\n", PP2t(target), tt, hoc_object_name(target_->ob));
3349  call_net_receive(ns);
3350 }

3359 void SelfEvent::call_net_receive(NetCvode* ns) {
3360  STATISTICS(selfevent_deliver_);
3361  POINT_RECEIVE(target_->prop->_type, target_, weight_, flag_);
3362  if (errno) {
3363  if (nrn_errno_check(target_->prop->_type)) {
3364  hoc_warning("errno set during SelfEvent deliver to NET_RECEIVE", (char*) 0);
3365  }
3366  }
3367  NetCvodeThreadData& nctd = ns->p[PP2NT(target_)->id];
3368  --nctd.unreffed_event_cnt_;
3369  nctd.sepool_->hpfree(this);
3370 }

3401 void NetCvode::local_retreat(double t, Cvode* cv) {
3402  if (!cvode_active_) {
3403  return;
3404  }
3405  TQueue* tq = p[cv->nth_ ? cv->nth_->id : 0].tq_;
3406  if (tq) {
3407 #if PRINT_EVENT
3408  if (print_event_) {
3409  Printf("microstep local retreat from %g (cvode_%p is at %g) for event onset=%g\n",
3410  cv->tqitem_->t_,
3411  cv,
3412  cv->t_,
3413  t);
3414  }
3415 #endif
3416  cv->interpolate(t);
3417  tq->move(cv->tqitem_, t);
3418 #if PRINT_EVENT
3419  if (print_event_ > 1) {
3420  Printf("after target solve time for %p is %g , dt=%g\n", cv, cv->time(), nt_dt);
3421  }
3422 #endif
3423  } else {
3424  assert(t == cv->t_ || (cv->tstop_begin_ <= t && t <= cv->tstop_end_));
3425  }
3426 }
3427 
3428 void NetCvode::retreat(double t, Cvode* cv) {
3429  if (!cvode_active_) {
3430  return;
3431  }
3432  TQueue* tq = p[cv->nth_ ? cv->nth_->id : 0].tq_;
3433 #if PRINT_EVENT
3434  if (print_event_) {
3435  Printf("microstep retreat from %g (cvode_%p is at %g) for event onset=%g\n",
3436  tq ? cv->tqitem_->t_ : cv->t_,
3437  cv,
3438  cv->t_,
3439  t);
3440  }
3441 #endif
3442  cv->interpolate(t);
3443  if (tq) {
3444  tq->move(cv->tqitem_, t);
3445  }
3446 #if PRINT_EVENT
3447  if (print_event_ > 1) {
3448  Printf("after target solve time for %p is %g , dt=%g\n", cv, cv->time(), dt);
3449  }
3450 #endif
3451 }

3454 
3455 bool neosim_deliver_self_events(TQueue* tqe, double til);
3456 bool neosim_deliver_self_events(TQueue* tqe, double til) {
3457  bool b;
3458  TQItem* q;
3459  DiscreteEvent* d;
3460  b = false;
3461  while (tqe->least_t() <= til + .5e-8) {
3462  b = true;
3463  q = tqe->least();
3464  t = q->t_;
3465  d = (DiscreteEvent*) q->data_;
3466  assert(d->type() == SelfEventType);
3467  tqe->remove(q);
3468  d->deliver(t, net_cvode_instance);
3469  }
3470 }
3471 
3472 void neosim2nrn_advance(void* e, void* v, double tout) {
3473  neosim_entity_ = e;
3474  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
3475  TQueue* tqe;
3476 
3477  // now can integrate to tout since it is guaranteed there will
3478  // be no further real events to this cell before tout.
3479  // but we must handle self events. The implementation is
3480  // analogous to the NetCvode::solve with single and tout
3481  Cvode* cv = (Cvode*) d->target_->nvi_; // so self event from INITIAL block
3482  tqe = cv->neosim_self_events_;
3483  // not a bug even if there is no BREAKPOINT block. I.e.
3484  // artificial cells will work.
3485  t = cv->time();
3486  while (tout > t) {
3487  do {
3488  cv->check_deliver();
3489  } while (neosim_deliver_self_events(tqe, t));
3490  cv->solve();
3491  }
3492  cv->interpolate(tout);
3493  cv->check_deliver();
3494 }
3495 
3496 void neosim2nrn_deliver(void* e, void* v) {
3497  neosim_entity_ = e;
3498  NetCon* d = (NetCon*) v;
3499  Cvode* cv = (Cvode*) d->target_->nvi_;
3500  d->deliver(cv->t_, net_cvode_instance);
3501 }
3502 
3503 #endif
3504 
3505 // parallel global variable time-step
3506 int NetCvode::pgvts(double tstop) {
3507  int err = NVI_SUCCESS;
3508  double tt = nt_t;
3509  while (tt < tstop && !stoprun && err == NVI_SUCCESS) {
3510  err = pgvts_event(tt);
3511  }
3512  return err;
3513 }
3514 
3515 // parallel global variable time-step event handling
3516 // return is what cvode call to make and the value of tt to make it at
3517 // in response to the next global event. We try to do only one
3518 // allreduce for a given event. Since all processes have to stay together
3519 // with respect to cvode, we have to factor out those calls from the
3520 // classical DiscreteEvent::deliver methods. I.e. deliver can only
3521 // deliver an event, it cannot interpolate, etc.
3522 // Assume events are sparse and handle them one at a time.
3523 int NetCvode::pgvts_event(double& tt) {
3524  int op, err, init;
3525  DiscreteEvent* de;
3526  assert(gcv_);
3527  de = pgvts_least(tt, op, init);
3528  err = pgvts_cvode(tt, op);
3529  if (init) {
3530  gcv_->set_init_flag();
3531  }
3532  if (de) { // handle the event and others just like it
3533  de->pgvts_deliver(tt, this);
3534  while (p[0].tqe_->least_t() == tt) {
3535  TQItem* q = p[0].tqe_->least();
3536  de = (DiscreteEvent*) q->data_;
3537  int i1;
3538  if (de->pgvts_op(i1) == op && i1 == init) {
3539  p[0].tqe_->remove(q);
3540  de->pgvts_deliver(tt, this);
3541  } else {
3542  break;
3543  }
3544  }
3545  }
3546  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
3547  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
3548  }
3549  return err;
3550 }
3551 
3552 DiscreteEvent* NetCvode::pgvts_least(double& tt, int& op, int& init) {
3553  DiscreteEvent* de = nullptr;
3554 #if NRNMPI
3555  TQItem* q = nullptr;
3556  if (gcv_->initialize_ && p[0].tqe_->least_t() > gcv_->t_) {
3557  tt = gcv_->t_;
3558  op = 3;
3559  init = 0;
3560  } else if (gcv_->tn_ < p[0].tqe_->least_t()) {
3561  tt = gcv_->tn_;
3562  op = 1;
3563  init = 0;
3564  } else {
3565  // If there are several events at the same time we need the
3566  // highest priority (in particular, NetParEvent last).
3567  // This is due to the fact that NetParEvent.deliver
3568  // handles all the events at that time so there better not
3569  // be any after it on the queue.
3570  q = p[0].tqe_->least();
3571  if (q) {
3572  de = (DiscreteEvent*) q->data_;
3573  tt = q->t_;
3574  op = de->pgvts_op(init);
3575  if (op == 4) { // is there another event at the same time?
3576  TQItem* q2 = p[0].tqe_->second_least(tt);
3577  if (q2) {
3578  q = q2;
3579  de = (DiscreteEvent*) q2->data_;
3580  op = de->pgvts_op(init);
3581  assert(op != 4);
3582  // printf("%d Type %d event after NetParEvent with deliver %g and t=%g\n",
3583  // nrnmpi_myid, de->type(), tt, gcv_->t_);
3584  }
3585  }
3586  } else {
3587  tt = 1e20;
3588  op = 1;
3589  init = 0;
3590  }
3591  }
3592  double ts = tt;
3593  int ops = op;
3594  if (nrnmpi_pgvts_least(&tt, &op, &init)) {
3595  if (q) {
3596  p[0].tqe_->remove(q);
3597  }
3598  } else if (op == 4) { // NetParEvent need to be done all together
3599  p[0].tqe_->remove(q);
3600  } else if (ts == tt && q && ops == op) { // safe to do this event as well
3601  p[0].tqe_->remove(q);
3602  } else {
3603  de = nullptr;
3604  }
3605 #endif
3606  return de;
3607 }
3608 
3609 int NetCvode::pgvts_cvode(double tt, int op) {
3610  int err = NVI_SUCCESS;
3611  // this is the only place where we can enter cvode
3612  switch (op) {
3613  case 1: // advance
3614  if (condition_order() == 1) {
3615  gcv_->check_deliver();
3616  }
3617  gcv_->record_continuous();
3618  err = gcv_->advance_tn(nrn_ensure_model_data_are_sorted());
3619  if (condition_order() == 2) {
3620  gcv_->evaluate_conditions();
3621  }
3622  break;
3623  case 2: // interpolate
3624  err = gcv_->interpolate(tt);
3625  break;
3626  case 3: // initialize
3627  err = gcv_->init(tt);
3628  initialized_ = true;
3629  if (condition_order() == 2) {
3630  gcv_->evaluate_conditions();
3631  }
3632  break;
3633  }
3634  return err;
3635 }
3636 
3637 bool NetCvode::use_partrans() {
3638 #if NRNMPI
3639  if (gcv_) {
3640  return gcv_->use_partrans_;
3641  } else {
3642  return 0;
3643  }
3644 #endif
3645  return 0;
3646 }
3647 
3648 void ncs2nrn_integrate(double tstop) {
3649  double ts;
3650  nrn_use_busywait(1); // just a possibility
3651  auto const cache_token = nrn_ensure_model_data_are_sorted();
3652  if (cvode_active_) {
3653 #if NRNMPI
3654  if (net_cvode_instance->use_partrans()) {
3655  net_cvode_instance->pgvts(tstop);
3656  t = nt_t;
3657  dt = nt_dt;
3658  } else
3659 #endif
3660  {
3661  net_cvode_instance->solve(tstop);
3662  t = nt_t;
3663  dt = nt_dt;
3664  }
3665  } else {
3666 #if 1
3667  int n = (int) ((tstop - nt_t) / dt + 1e-9);
3668  if (n > 3 && !nrnthread_v_transfer_) {
3669  nrn_fixed_step_group(cache_token, n);
3670  } else
3671 #endif
3672  {
3673 #if NRNMPI && !defined(USENCS)
3674  ts = tstop - dt;
3675  assert(nt_t <= tstop);
3676  // It may very well be the case that we do not advance at all
3677  while (nt_t <= ts) {
3678 #else
3679  ts = tstop - .5 * dt;
3680  while (nt_t < ts) {
3681 #endif
3682  nrn_fixed_step(cache_token);
3683  if (stoprun) {
3684  break;
3685  }
3686  }
3687  }
3688  }
3689  // handle all the pending flag=1 self events
3690  for (int i = 0; i < nrn_nthread; ++i) {
3691  assert(nrn_threads[i]._t == nt_t);
3692  }
3693  all_pending_selfqueue(nt_t);
3694  nrn_use_busywait(0); // certainly not
3695 }
3696 
3697 TQueue* NetCvode::event_queue(NrnThread* nt) {
3698  return p[nt->id].tqe_;
3699 }

3701 static double pending_selfqueue_deliver_;
3702 static void* pending_selfqueue(NrnThread* nt) {
3703  nrn_pending_selfqueue(pending_selfqueue_deliver_, nt);
3704  return 0;
3705 }
3706 
3707 void nrn_pending_selfqueue(double tt, NrnThread* nt) {
3708  NetCvodeThreadData& nctd = net_cvode_instance->p[nt->id];
3709  double ts = nt->_t;
3710  // net_cvode_instance->deliver_events(nctd.immediate_deliver_, nt);
3711  SelfQueue* sq = nctd.selfqueue_;
3712  TQItem *q1, *q2;
3713  nctd.immediate_deliver_ = tt;
3714  for (q1 = sq->first(); q1; q1 = q2) {
3715  if (q1->t_ <= tt) {
3716  SelfEvent* se = (SelfEvent*) q1->data_;
3717  // printf("ncs2nrn_integrate %g SelfEvent for %s at %g\n", tstop,
3718  // hoc_object_name(se->target_->ob), q1->t_);
3719  se->deliver(q1->t_, net_cvode_instance, nt);
3720  // could it add another self-event?, check before removal
3721  q2 = sq->next(q1);
3722  sq->remove(q1);
3723  } else {
3724  q2 = sq->next(q1);
3725  }
3726  }
3727  assert(nctd.tqe_->least_t() >= tt);
3728  nt->_t = ts;
3729  nctd.immediate_deliver_ = -1e100;
3730 }
3731 
3732 // only the main thread can calls this
3733 static void all_pending_selfqueue(double tt) {
3734  if (nrn_use_selfqueue_) {
3735  nrn_wait_for_threads();
3736  // for (int i=0; i < nrn_nthread; ++i) { assert(nrn_threads[i]._t == nt_t);}
3737  pending_selfqueue_deliver_ = tt;
3738  nrn_multithread_job(pending_selfqueue);
3739  }
3740 }

3873 void NetCvode::solver_prepare() {

3902  playrec_setup();
3903  }
3904 }

3906 void NetCvode::re_init(double t) {
3907  int i, j;
3908  if (nrn_modeltype() == 0) {
3909  if (gcv_) {
3910  gcv_->t_ = t;
3911  gcv_->tn_ = t;
3912  } else {
3913  lvardtloop(i, j) {
3914  Cvode& cv = p[i].lcv_[j];
3915  cv.t_ = t;
3916  cv.tn_ = t;
3917  }
3918  }
3919  return;
3920  }
3921  double dtsav = nt_dt;
3922  solver_prepare();
3923  if (gcv_) {
3924  gcv_->stat_init();
3925  gcv_->init(t);
3926  if (condition_order() == 2) {
3927  gcv_->evaluate_conditions();
3928  }
3929  } else {
3930  lvardtloop(i, j) {
3931  Cvode& cv = p[i].lcv_[j];
3932  cv.stat_init();
3933  cv.init(t);
3934  cv.tqitem_->t_ = t;
3935  if (condition_order() == 2) {
3936  cv.evaluate_conditions();
3937  }
3938  }
3939  }

3941 }
3942 
3943 void NetCvode::fornetcon_prepare() {
3944  NrnThread* nt;
3945  NrnThreadMembList* tml;
3946  if (fornetcon_change_cnt_ == structure_change_cnt) {
3947  return;
3948  }
3949  fornetcon_change_cnt_ = structure_change_cnt;
3950  if (nrn_fornetcon_cnt_ == 0) {
3951  return;
3952  }
3953  int i, j;
3954  // initialize a map from type to dparam index, -1 means no FOR_NETCONS statement
3955  std::vector<int> t2i(n_memb_func, -1);
3956  // create ForNetConsInfo in all the relevant point processes
3957  // and fill in the t2i map.
3958  for (i = 0; i < nrn_fornetcon_cnt_; ++i) {
3959  int index = nrn_fornetcon_index_[i];
3960  int type = nrn_fornetcon_type_[i];
3961  t2i[type] = index;
3962  if (nrn_is_artificial_[type]) {
3963  auto* const m = &memb_list[type];
3964  for (j = 0; j < m->nodecount; ++j) {
3965  // Save ForNetConsInfo* as void* to avoid needing to expose the
3966  // definition of ForNetConsInfo to translated MOD file code
3967  void** v = &(m->pdata[j][index].literal_value<void*>());
3968  _nrn_free_fornetcon(v);
3969  ForNetConsInfo* fnc = new ForNetConsInfo;
3970  *v = fnc;
3971  fnc->argslist = 0;
3972  fnc->size = 0;
3973  }
3974  } else {
3975  FOR_THREADS(nt) for (tml = nt->tml; tml; tml = tml->next) if (tml->index == type) {
3976  Memb_list* m = tml->ml;
3977  for (j = 0; j < m->nodecount; ++j) {
3978  void** v = &(m->pdata[j][index].literal_value<void*>());
3979  _nrn_free_fornetcon(v);
3980  ForNetConsInfo* fnc = new ForNetConsInfo;
3981  *v = fnc;
3982  fnc->argslist = 0;
3983  fnc->size = 0;
3984  }
3985  }
3986  }
3987  }
3988  // two loops over all netcons. one to count, one to fill in argslist
3989  // count
3990  hoc_Item* q;
3991  if (psl_)
3992  ITERATE(q, psl_) {
3993  PreSyn* ps = (PreSyn*) VOIDITM(q);
3994  const NetConPList& dil = ps->dil_;
3995  for (const auto& d1: dil) {
3996  Point_process* pnt = d1->target_;
3997  if (pnt && t2i[pnt->prop->_type] > -1) {
3998  auto* fnc = static_cast<ForNetConsInfo*>(
3999  pnt->prop->dparam[t2i[pnt->prop->_type]].get<void*>());
4000  assert(fnc);
4001  fnc->size += 1;
4002  }
4003  }
4004  }
4005 
4006  // allocate argslist space and initialize for another count
4007  for (i = 0; i < nrn_fornetcon_cnt_; ++i) {
4008  int index = nrn_fornetcon_index_[i];
4009  int type = nrn_fornetcon_type_[i];
4010  if (nrn_is_artificial_[type]) {
4011  auto* const m = &memb_list[type];
4012  for (j = 0; j < m->nodecount; ++j) {
4013  auto* fnc = static_cast<ForNetConsInfo*>(m->pdata[j][index].get<void*>());
4014  if (fnc->size > 0) {
4015  fnc->argslist = new double*[fnc->size];
4016  fnc->size = 0;
4017  }
4018  }
4019  } else {
4020  FOR_THREADS(nt)
4021  for (tml = nt->tml; tml; tml = tml->next)
4022  if (tml->index == nrn_fornetcon_type_[i]) {
4023  Memb_list* m = tml->ml;
4024  for (j = 0; j < m->nodecount; ++j) {
4025  auto* fnc = static_cast<ForNetConsInfo*>(m->pdata[j][index].get<void*>());
4026  if (fnc->size > 0) {
4027  fnc->argslist = new double*[fnc->size];
4028  fnc->size = 0;
4029  }
4030  }
4031  }
4032  }
4033  }
4034  // fill in argslist and count again
4035  if (psl_) {
4036  ITERATE(q, psl_) {
4037  PreSyn* ps = (PreSyn*) VOIDITM(q);
4038  const NetConPList& dil = ps->dil_;
4039  for (const auto& d1: dil) {
4040  Point_process* pnt = d1->target_;
4041  if (pnt && t2i[pnt->prop->_type] > -1) {
4042  auto* fnc = static_cast<ForNetConsInfo*>(
4043  pnt->prop->dparam[t2i[pnt->prop->_type]].get<void*>());
4044  fnc->argslist[fnc->size] = d1->weight_;
4045  fnc->size += 1;
4046  }

4094 int NetCvode::cellindex() {
4095  Section* sec = chk_access();
4096  int i, j, ii;
4097  if (single_) {
4098  return 0;
4099  } else {
4100  ii = 0;
4101  lvardtloop(i, j) {
4102  if (sec == p[i].lcv_[j].ctd_[0].v_node_[p[i].lcv_[j].ctd_[0].rootnodecount_]->sec) {
4103  return ii;
4104  }
4105  ii++;
4106  }
4107  }
4108  hoc_execerror(secname(sec), " is not the root section for any local step cvode instance");
4109  return 0;
4110 }

4112 void NetCvode::states() {
4113  Vect* v = vector_arg(1);
4114  if (!cvode_active_) {
4115  v->resize(0);
4116  return;
4117  }
4118  int n{};
4119  if (gcv_) {
4120  n += gcv_->neq_;
4121  } else {
4122  int i, j;
4123  lvardtloop(i, j) {
4124  n += p[i].lcv_[j].neq_;
4125  }
4126  }
4127  v->resize(n);
4128  double* vp{vector_vec(v)};
4129  if (gcv_) {
4130  gcv_->states(vp);
4131  } else {
4132  int i{}, j{}, k{};
4133  lvardtloop(i, j) {
4134  p[i].lcv_[j].states(vp + k);
4135  k += p[i].lcv_[j].neq_;
4136  }
4137  }
4138 }

4179 double nrn_hoc2fun(void* v) {

4182  Vect* s = vector_arg(2);
4183  Vect* ds = vector_arg(3);

4185  hoc_execerror("not global variable time step", 0);
4186  }

4188  hoc_execerror("size of state vector != number of state equations", 0);
4189  }
4190  if (nrn_nthread > 1) {
4191  hoc_execerror("only one thread allowed", 0);
4192  }
4193  ds->resize(s->size());
4194  nrn_cvfun(tt, vector_vec(s), vector_vec(ds));
4195  return 0.;
4196 }

4286 /** @brief Create a lookup table for variable names.
4287  *
4288  * This is only created on-demand because it involves building a lookup table
4289  * of pointers, some of which are obtained from data_handles (and are therefore
4290  * unstable). Eventually the operator<< of data_handle might provide the
4291  * necessary functionality and this could be dropped completely.
4292  */
4293 HocDataPaths NetCvode::create_hdp(int style) {
4294  int n{};
4295  if (gcv_) {
4296  n += gcv_->neq_;
4297  } else {
4298  int i, j;
4299  lvardtloop(i, j) {
4300  n += p[i].lcv_[j].neq_;
4301  }
4302  }
4303  HocDataPaths hdp{2 * n, style};
4304  if (gcv_) {
4305  for (int it = 0; it < nrn_nthread; ++it) {
4306  CvodeThreadData& z = gcv_->ctd_[it];
4307  for (int j = 0; j < z.nonvint_extra_offset_; ++j) {
4308  hdp.append(static_cast<double*>(z.pv_[j]));
4309  }
4310  }
4311  } else {
4312  int i, it;
4313  lvardtloop(it, i) {
4314  auto const neq = p[it].lcv_[i].ctd_[0].nvsize_;
4315  auto& pv = p[it].lcv_[i].ctd_[0].pv_;
4316  for (int j = 0; j < neq; ++j) {
4317  hdp.append(static_cast<double*>(pv[j]));
4318  }
4319  }
4320  }
4321  hdp.search();
4322  return hdp;
4323 }
4324 
4325 std::string NetCvode::statename(int is, int style) {
4326  if (!cvode_active_) {
4327  hoc_execerror("Cvode is not active", 0);
4328  }
4329  auto const n = [&]() {
4330  int n{};
4331  if (gcv_) {
4332  n += gcv_->neq_;
4333  } else {
4334  int i, j;
4335  lvardtloop(i, j) {
4336  n += p[i].lcv_[j].neq_;
4337  }
4338  }
4339  return n;
4340  }();
4341  if (is >= n) {
4342  hoc_execerror("Cvode::statename argument out of range", nullptr);
4343  }
4344  auto const impl = [hdp = create_hdp(style), style, this](auto& handle) -> std::string {
4345  auto* const raw_ptr = static_cast<double*>(handle);
4346  if (style == 2) {
4347  auto* sym = hdp.retrieve_sym(raw_ptr);
4348  assert(sym);
4349  return sym2name(sym);
4350  } else {
4351  std::string s = hdp.retrieve(raw_ptr);
4352  return !s.empty() ? s.c_str() : "unknown";
4353  }
4354  };
4355  int j{};
4356  if (gcv_) {
4357  for (int it = 0; it < nrn_nthread; ++it) {
4358  CvodeThreadData& z = gcv_->ctd_[it];
4359  if (j + z.nvoffset_ + z.nvsize_ > is) {
4360  return impl(z.pv_[is - j]);
4361  }
4362  j += z.nvsize_;
4363  }
4364  } else {
4365  int it, i;
4366  lvardtloop(it, i) {
4367  if (j + p[it].lcv_[i].neq_ > is) {
4368  CvodeThreadData& z = p[it].lcv_[i].ctd_[0];
4369  return impl(z.pv_[is - j]);
4370  }
4371  j += p[it].lcv_[i].neq_;
4372  }
4373  }
4374  return "unknown";
4375 }
4376 
4377 const char* NetCvode::sym2name(Symbol* sym) {
4378  if (sym->type == RANGEVAR && sym->u.rng.type > 1 && memb_func[sym->u.rng.type].is_point) {
4379  static char buf[200];
4380  Sprintf(buf, "%s.%s", memb_func[sym->u.rng.type].sym->name, sym->name);
4381  return buf;
4382  } else {
4383  return sym->name;
4384  }
4385 }
4386 
4387 Symbol* NetCvode::name2sym(const char* name) {
4388  std::vector<char> buf(strlen(name) + 1);
4389  strcpy(buf.data(), name);
4390  char* cp;
4391  for (cp = buf.data(); *cp; ++cp) {
4392  if (*cp == '.') {
4393  *cp = '\0';
4394  ++cp;
4395  break;
4396  }
4397  }
4398  Symbol* sym = hoc_table_lookup(buf.data(), hoc_built_in_symlist);
4399  if (!sym) {
4400  sym = hoc_table_lookup(buf.data(), hoc_top_level_symlist);
4401  }
4402  if (sym && *cp == '\0' && (sym->type == RANGEVAR || strcmp(sym->name, "Vector") == 0)) {
4403  return sym;
4404  } else if (sym && sym->type == TEMPLATE && *cp != '\0') {
4405  sym = hoc_table_lookup(cp, sym->u.ctemplate->symtable);
4406  if (sym) {
4407  return sym;
4408  }
4409  }
4410  hoc_execerror(name, "must be in form rangevar or Template.var");
4411  return nullptr;
4412 }

4496 NetCon* NetCvode::install_deliver(neuron::container::data_handle<double> dsrc,
4497  Section* ssrc,
4498  Object* osrc,
4499  Object* target,
4500  double threshold,
4501  double delay,
4502  double magnitude) {
4503  PreSyn* ps = nullptr;
4504  neuron::container::data_handle<double> psrc{};
4505  if (ssrc) {
4506  consist_sec_pd("NetCon", ssrc, dsrc);
4507  }
4508  if (!pst_) {
4509  pst_ = new PreSynTable(1000);
4510  pst_cnt_ = 0;
4511  }
4512  if (!psl_) {
4513  psl_ = hoc_l_newlist();
4514  }
4515  if (osrc) {
4516  assert(!dsrc);
4517  char buf[256];
4518  if (hoc_table_lookup("x", osrc->ctemplate->symtable)) {
4519  Point_process* pp = ob2pntproc(osrc);
4520  assert(pp && pp->prop);
4521  if (!pnt_receive[pp->prop->_type]) { // only if no NET_RECEIVE block
4522  Sprintf(buf, "%s.x", hoc_object_name(osrc));
4523  psrc = hoc_val_handle(buf);
4524  }
4525  }
4526  } else {
4527  psrc = dsrc;
4528  }
4529  if (psrc) {
4530  auto psti = pst_->find(psrc);
4531  if (psti == pst_->end()) {
4532  ps = new PreSyn(psrc, osrc, ssrc);
4533  ps->hi_ = hoc_l_insertvoid(psl_, ps);
4534  (*pst_)[psrc] = ps;
4535  ++pst_cnt_;
4536  } else {
4537  ps = psti->second;
4538  }
4539  if (threshold != -1e9) {
4540  ps->threshold_ = threshold;
4541  }
4542  } else if (osrc) {
4543  Point_process* pnt = ob2pntproc(osrc);
4544  if (pnt->presyn_) {
4545  ps = (PreSyn*) pnt->presyn_;
4546  } else {
4547  ps = new PreSyn(psrc, osrc, ssrc);
4548  if (threshold != -1e9) {
4549  ps->threshold_ = threshold;
4550  }
4551  ps->hi_ = hoc_l_insertvoid(psl_, ps);
4552  pnt->presyn_ = ps;
4553  }
4554  } else if (target) { // no source so use the special presyn
4555  if (!unused_presyn) {
4556  unused_presyn = new PreSyn({}, nullptr, nullptr);
4557  unused_presyn->hi_ = hoc_l_insertvoid(psl_, unused_presyn);
4558  }
4559  ps = unused_presyn;
4560  }
4561  ps_thread_link(ps);
4562  NetCon* d = new NetCon(ps, target);
4563  d->delay_ = delay;
4564  d->weight_[0] = magnitude;
4565  structure_change_cnt_ = 0;
4566  return d;
4567 }

4574 }

4576 void NetCvode::presyn_disconnect(PreSyn* ps) {
4577  if (ps == unused_presyn) {
4578  unused_presyn = nullptr;
4579  }
4580  if (ps->hi_) {
4581  hoc_l_delete(ps->hi_);
4582  ps->hi_ = nullptr;
4583  }
4584  if (ps->hi_th_) {
4585  hoc_l_delete(ps->hi_th_);
4586  ps->hi_th_ = nullptr;
4587  }
4588  if (ps->thvar_) {
4589  --pst_cnt_;
4590  pst_->erase(ps->thvar_);
4591  ps->thvar_ = {};
4592  }
4593  if (gcv_) {
4594  for (int it = 0; it < gcv_->nctd_; ++it) {
4595  PreSynList* psl = gcv_->ctd_[it].psl_th_;
4596  if (psl)
4597  for (size_t j = 0; j < psl->size(); ++j) {
4598  if ((*psl)[j] == ps) {
4599  psl->erase(psl->begin() + j);
4600  return;
4601  }
4602  }
4603  }
4604  } else {
4605  int i, j;
4606  lvardtloop(i, j) {
4607  PreSynList* psl = p[i].lcv_[j].ctd_[0].psl_th_;
4608  if (psl)
4609  for (size_t j = 0; j < psl->size(); ++j) {
4610  if ((*psl)[j] == ps) {
4611  psl->erase(psl->begin() + j);
4612  return;
4613  }
4614  }
4615  }
4616  }
4617 }

4645 NetCon::NetCon(PreSyn* src, Object* target) {
4646  NetConSave::invalid();
4647  obj_ = nullptr;
4648  src_ = src;
4649  delay_ = 1.0;
4650  if (src_) {
4651  src_->dil_.push_back(this);
4652  src_->use_min_delay_ = 0;
4653  }
4654  if (target == nullptr) {
4655  target_ = nullptr;
4656  active_ = false;
4657  cnt_ = 1;
4658  weight_ = new double[cnt_];
4659  weight_[0] = 0.0;
4660  return;
4661  }
4662  target_ = ob2pntproc(target);
4663  active_ = true;
4664 #if DISCRETE_EVENT_OBSERVER
4665  ObjObservable::Attach(target, this);
4666 #endif
4667  if (!pnt_receive[target_->prop->_type]) {
4668  hoc_execerror("No NET_RECEIVE in target PointProcess:", hoc_object_name(target));
4669  }
4670  cnt_ = pnt_receive_size[target_->prop->_type];
4671  weight_ = nullptr;
4672  if (cnt_) {
4673  weight_ = new double[cnt_];
4674  for (int i = 0; i < cnt_; ++i) {
4675  weight_[i] = 0.0;
4676  }
4677  }
4678 }
4679 
4680 NetCon::~NetCon() {
4681  // printf("~NetCon\n");
4682  NetConSave::invalid();
4683  rmsrc();
4684  if (cnt_) {
4685  delete[] weight_;
4686  }
4687 #if DISCRETE_EVENT_OBSERVER
4688  if (target_) {
4689  ObjObservable::Detach(target_->ob, this);
4690  }
4691 #endif
4692 }
4693 
4694 void NetCon::rmsrc() {
4695  if (src_) {
4696  for (size_t i = 0; i < src_->dil_.size(); ++i) {
4697  if (src_->dil_[i] == this) {
4698  src_->dil_.erase(src_->dil_.begin() + i);
4699  if (src_->dil_.size() == 0 && src_->tvec_ == NULL && src_->idvec_ == NULL) {
4700  if (src_->output_index_ == -1) {
4701  delete std::exchange(src_, nullptr);
4702  }
4703  }
4704  break;
4705  }
4706  }
4707  }
4708  src_ = nullptr;
4709 }

4766 NetCon* NetConSave::weight2netcon(double* pd) {
4767  NetCon* nc;
4768  if (!wtable_) {
4769  hoc_Item* q;
4770  Symbol* sym = hoc_lookup("NetCon");
4771  wtable_ = new NetConSaveWeightTable(2 * sym->u.ctemplate->count);
4772  ITERATE(q, sym->u.ctemplate->olist) {
4773  Object* obj = OBJ(q);
4774  nc = (NetCon*) obj->u.this_pointer;
4775  if (nc->weight_) {
4776  (*wtable_)[nc->weight_] = nc;
4777  }
4778  }
4779  }
4780  auto wti = wtable_->find(pd);
4781  if (wti != wtable_->end()) {
4782  nc = wti->second;
4783  assert(nc->weight_ == pd);
4784  return nc;
4785  } else {
4786  return nullptr;
4787  }
4788 }

4818 void NetCvode::ps_thread_link(PreSyn* ps) {
4819  if (!ps) {
4820  return;
4821  }
4822  ps->nt_ = nullptr;
4823  if (!v_structure_change) { // PP2NT etc are correct
4824  if (ps->osrc_) {
4825  ps->nt_ = PP2NT(ob2pntproc(ps->osrc_));
4826  } else if (ps->ssrc_) {
4827  ps->nt_ = ps->ssrc_->prop->dparam[9].get<NrnThread*>();
4828  }
4829  }
4830  if (!ps->nt_) { // premature, reorder_secorder() not called yet
4831  return;
4832  }
4833  if (ps->thvar_) {
4834  int i = ps->nt_->id;
4835  if (!p[i].psl_thr_) {
4836  p[i].psl_thr_ = hoc_l_newlist();
4837  }
4838  ps->hi_th_ = hoc_l_insertvoid(p[i].psl_thr_, ps);
4839  }
4840 }

4842 void NetCvode::update_ps2nt() {
4843  int i;
4844  // first, opportunistically create p[]
4845  p_construct(nrn_nthread);
4846  // iterate over all threshold PreSyn and fill the NrnThread field
4847  hoc_Item* q;
4848  for (i = 0; i < nrn_nthread; ++i) {
4849  if (p[i].psl_thr_) {
4850  hoc_l_freelist(&p[i].psl_thr_);
4851  }
4852  }
4853  if (psl_)
4854  ITERATE(q, psl_) {
4855  PreSyn* ps = (PreSyn*) VOIDITM(q);
4856  ps_thread_link(ps);
4857  }
4858 }

5065 void PreSyn::record(double tt) {
5066  if (tvec_) {
5067  // need to lock the vector if shared by other PreSyn
5068  // since we get here in the thread that manages the
5069  // threshold detection (or net_event from NET_RECEIVE).
5070  if (idvec_) {
5071  tvec_->lock();
5072  }
5073  tvec_->push_back(tt);
5074  if (idvec_) {
5075  idvec_->push_back(rec_id_);
5076  tvec_->unlock();
5077  }
5078  }
5079  if (stmt_) {
5080  if (nrn_nthread > 1) {
5081  nrn_hoc_lock();
5082  }
5083  t = tt;
5084  stmt_->execute(false);
5085  if (nrn_nthread > 1) {
5086  nrn_hoc_unlock();
5087  }
5088  }
5089 }

5094  tvec_ = nullptr;
5095  }
5096  if (idvec_ && idvec_->obj_ == ((ObjObservable*) o)->object()) {
5097  idvec_ = nullptr;
5098  }
5099  if (dil_.size() == 0 && tvec_ == nullptr && idvec_ == nullptr && output_index_ == -1) {
5100  delete this;
5101  }
5102 }

5133 void ConditionEvent::check(NrnThread* nt, double tt, double teps) {
5134  if (value() > 0.0) {
5135  if (flag_ == false) {
5136  flag_ = true;
5137  valthresh_ = 0.;
5138 #if USENEOSIM
5139  if (neosim_entity_) {
5140  (*p_nrn2neosim_send)(neosim_entity_, tt);
5141  } else {
5142 #endif
5143  send(tt + teps, net_cvode_instance, nt);
5144 #if USENEOSIM
5145  }
5146 #endif
5147  }
5148  } else {
5149  flag_ = false;
5150  }
5151 }

5153 ConditionEvent::ConditionEvent() {
5154  qthresh_ = NULL;
5155  valold_ = 0.0;
5156 }
5157 ConditionEvent::~ConditionEvent() {}
5158 
5159 void ConditionEvent::condition(Cvode* cv) { // logic for high order threshold detection
5160  // printf("ConditionEvent::condition f=%d t=%20.15g v=%20.15g\n", flag_, t, value());
5161  NrnThread* nt = thread();
5162  if (qthresh_) { // the threshold event has not
5163  // been handled. i.e. the cell must have retreated to
5164  // a time not later than the threshold time.
5165  assert(nt->_t <= qthresh_->t_);
5166  abandon_statistics(cv);
5167  // abandon the event
5168  STATISTICS(abandon_);
5169  net_cvode_instance->remove_event(qthresh_, nt->id);
5170  qthresh_ = nullptr;
5171  valthresh_ = 0.;
5172  flag_ = false;
5173  }
5174 
5175  double val = value();
5176  if (flag_ == false && val >= 0.0) { // above threshold
5177  flag_ = true;
5178  valthresh_ = 0.;
5179  if (cv->t0_ == cv->tn_) { // inited
5180  // means immediate threshold event now.
5181  // no need for qthresh since there is
5182  // no question of abandoning it so instead
5183  // of a qthresh it is a send event.
5184  STATISTICS(init_above_);
5185  send(nt->_t, net_cvode_instance, nt);
5186  } else { // crossed somewhere in the told to t interval
5187  STATISTICS(send_qthresh_);
5188  // reset the flag_ when the value goes lower than
5189  // valold since value() when qthresh_ handled
5190  // may in fact be below 0.0
5191  valthresh_ = valold_;
5192  double th = -valold_ / (val - valold_);
5193  th = th * nt->_t + (1. - th) * told_;
5194  assert(th >= cv->t0_ && th <= cv->tn_);
5195  qthresh_ = net_cvode_instance->event(th, this, nt);
5196  }
5197  } else if (flag_ == true && valold_ < valthresh_ && val < valthresh_) {
5198  // below threshold
5199  // previous step crossed in negative direction
5200  // and there was not any retreat or initialization
5201  // to give spurious crossing.
5202  flag_ = false;
5203  }
5204  valold_ = val;
5205  told_ = nt->_t;
5206 }
5207 
5208 double STECondition::value() {
5209  double val = stet_->value();
5210  return val;
5211 }
5212 
5213 void ConditionEvent::abandon_statistics(Cvode* cv) {
5214 #if 1
5215  // printf("ConditionEvent::condition %s t=%20.15g abandon event at %20.15g\n",
5216  // ssrc_?secname(ssrc_):"", t, qthresh_->t_);
5217  if (nt_t == qthresh_->t_) { // it is not clear whether
5218  // this could happen and if it does it may
5219  // take fastidiousness to
5220  // an extreme
5221  STATISTICS(eq_abandon_);
5222  Printf("abandon when t == qthresh_->t_ = %20.15g\n", nt_t);
5223  }
5224  if (cv->t0_ == cv->tn_) { // inited
5225  if (value() > 0.0) { // above threshold
5226  STATISTICS(abandon_init_above_);
5227  } else {
5228  STATISTICS(abandon_init_below_);
5229  }
5230  } else {
5231  if (value() > 0.0) { // above threshold
5232  STATISTICS(abandon_above_);
5233  } else {
5234  STATISTICS(abandon_below_);
5235  }
5236  }
5237 #endif
5238 }

5262 void WatchCondition::activate(double flag) {
5263  Cvode* cv = NULL;
5264  int id = 0;
5265  qthresh_ = nullptr;
5266  flag_ = (value() >= -hoc_epsilon) ? true : false;
5267  valthresh_ = 0.;
5268  nrflag_ = flag;
5269  if (!pnt_) { // possible for StateTransitionEvent
5270  // but only if 1 thread and no lvardt
5271  assert(nrn_nthread == 1);
5272  assert(net_cvode_instance->localstep() == false);
5273  cv = net_cvode_instance->gcv_;
5274  } else {
5275  cv = (Cvode*) pnt_->nvi_;
5276  }
5277  assert(cv);
5278  id = (cv->nctd_ > 1) ? thread()->id : 0;
5279  HTList*& wl = cv->ctd_[id].watch_list_;
5280  if (!wl) {
5281  wl = new HTList(nullptr);
5282  net_cvode_instance->wl_list_[id].push_back(wl);
5283  }
5284  Remove();
5285  wl->Append(this);
5286 }

5301 void WatchCondition::deliver(double tt, NetCvode* ns, NrnThread* nt) {
5302  if (qthresh_) {
5303  qthresh_ = nullptr;
5304  STATISTICS(deliver_qthresh_);
5305  }
5306  Cvode* cv = (Cvode*) pnt_->nvi_;
5307  int type = pnt_->prop->_type;
5308  if (cvode_active_ && cv) {
5309  ns->local_retreat(tt, cv);
5310  cv->set_init_flag();
5311  } else {
5312  PP2t(pnt_) = tt;
5313  }
5314  STATISTICS(watch_deliver_);
5315  POINT_RECEIVE(type, pnt_, nullptr, nrflag_);
5316  if (errno) {
5317  if (nrn_errno_check(type)) {
5318  hoc_warning("errno set during WatchCondition deliver to NET_RECEIVE", (char*) 0);
5319  }
5320  }
5321 }
5322 
5323 void StateTransitionEvent::transition(int src,
5324  int dest,
5325  neuron::container::data_handle<double> var1,
5326  neuron::container::data_handle<double> var2,
5327  std::unique_ptr<HocCommand> hc) {
5328  STETransition& st = states_[src].add_transition(pnt_);
5329  st.dest_ = dest;
5330  st.var1_ = std::move(var1);
5331  st.var2_ = std::move(var2);
5332  st.hc_ = std::move(hc);
5333  st.ste_ = this;
5334  st.var1_is_time_ = (static_cast<double*>(st.var1_) == &t);
5335 }

5357 void STECondition::deliver(double tt, NetCvode* ns, NrnThread* nt) {
5358  if (qthresh_) {
5359  qthresh_ = nullptr;
5360  STATISTICS(deliver_qthresh_);
5361  }
5362  if (!pnt_) {
5363  assert(nrn_nthread == 1 && ns->localstep() == false);
5364  if (cvode_active_) {
5365  Cvode* cv = ns->gcv_;
5366  ns->local_retreat(tt, cv);
5367  cv->set_init_flag();
5368  } else {
5369  nt->_t = tt;
5370  }
5371  } else {
5372  Cvode* cv = (Cvode*) pnt_->nvi_;
5373  if (cvode_active_ && cv) {
5374  ns->local_retreat(tt, cv);
5375  cv->set_init_flag();
5376  } else {
5377  PP2t(pnt_) = tt;
5378  }
5379  }
5380  STATISTICS(watch_deliver_);
5381  t = tt;
5382  stet_->event();
5383 }

5435 static Cvode* eval_cv;
5436 static void* eval_cond(NrnThread* nt) {
5437  eval_cv->evaluate_conditions(nt);
5438  return 0;
5439 }
5440 void Cvode::evaluate_conditions(NrnThread* nt) {
5441  if (!nt) {
5442  if (nrn_nthread > 1 && nctd_ > 1) {
5443  eval_cv = this;
5444  nrn_multithread_job(eval_cond);
5445  return;
5446  }
5447  nt = nrn_threads;
5448  }
5449  CvodeThreadData& z = CTD(nt->id);
5450  if (z.psl_th_) {
5451  // originally was a reverse iteration, but I thing that was
5452  // just to avoid continually calling count() on the List.
5453  for (auto ps: *(z.psl_th_)) {
5454  ps->condition(this);
5455  }
5456  }
5457  if (z.watch_list_) {
5458  for (HTList* item = z.watch_list_->First(); item != z.watch_list_->End();
5459  item = item->Next()) {
5460  ((WatchCondition*) item)->condition(this);
5461  }
5462  }
5463 }

5465 static void* chk_deliv(NrnThread* nt) {
5466  eval_cv->check_deliver(nt);
5467  return 0;
5468 }
5469 void Cvode::check_deliver(NrnThread* nt) {
5470  if (!nt) {
5471  if (nrn_nthread > 1) {
5472  eval_cv = this;
5473  nrn_multithread_job(chk_deliv);
5474  return;
5475  }
5476  nt = nrn_threads;
5477  }
5478  CvodeThreadData& z = CTD(nt->id);
5479  if (z.psl_th_) {
5480  // originally was a reverse iteration, but I thing that was
5481  // just to avoid continually calling count() on the List.
5482  for (auto ps: *(z.psl_th_)) {
5483  ps->check(nt, nt->_t);
5484  }
5485  }
5486  if (z.watch_list_) {
5487  for (HTList* item = z.watch_list_->First(); item != z.watch_list_->End();
5488  item = item->Next()) {
5489  ((WatchCondition*) item)->check(nt, nt->_t);
5490  }
5491  }
5492 }

5512 // nrnthread_get_trajectory_requests helper for buffered trajectories
5513 // also for per time step return (no Vector and varrays is NULL)
5514 // if bsize > 0 then CoreNEURON will write that number of values to the vectors.
5515 // If CoreNEURON has a start time > 0, (current value of t),
5516 // the amount to augment the vector depends
5517 // on the vector's current size in the current NEURON context and the
5518 // varray[i_trajec] double* will be determined by that current size.
5519 // However determination of whether to do per time step return or buffering
5520 // can be specified on the NEURON side.
5521 static int trajec_buffered(NrnThread& nt,
5522  int bsize,
5523  IvocVect* v,
5524  neuron::container::data_handle<double> pd,
5525  int i_pr,
5526  PlayRecord* pr,
5527  void** vpr,
5528  int i_trajec,
5529  int* types,
5530  int* indices,
5531  double** pvars,
5532  double** varrays) {
5533  int err = 0; // success
5534  if (bsize > 0) {
5535  int cur_size = v->size();
5536  if (v->buffer_size() < bsize + cur_size) {
5537  v->buffer_size(bsize + cur_size);
5538  }
5539  // nrnthread_trajectory_values will resize to correct size.
5540  v->resize(bsize + cur_size);
5541  varrays[i_trajec] = vector_vec(v) + cur_size; // begin filling here
5542  } else {
5543  // Danger, think this through better
5544  pvars[i_trajec] = static_cast<double*>(pd);
5545  }
5546  vpr[i_pr] = pr;
5547  if (static_cast<double const*>(pd) == &nt._t) {
5548  types[i_trajec] = 0;
5549  indices[i_trajec] = 0;
5550  } else {
5551  err = nrn_dblpntr2nrncore(pd, nt, types[i_trajec], indices[i_trajec]);
5552  if (err) {
5553  Fprintf(stderr,
5554  "Pointer %p of PlayRecord type %d ignored because not a Range Variable",
5555  static_cast<double*>(pd),
5556  pr->type());
5557  }
5558  }
5559  return err;
5560 }
5561 
5562 // Transfer of trajectories from CoreNEURON to NEURON.
5563 // bsize == 0: Most flexible interactivity, transfer on a per time step basis.
5564 // bsize > 0: Greatest performance, fill the entire trajectory arrays on
5565 // the CoreNEURON side and transferring at the end of a CoreNEURON run.
5566 // Here, we ensure the arrays have at least bsize size (i.e. at least tstop/dt)
5567 // beyond their current size and CoreNEURON will start filling from the
5568 // current fill time, h.t, location of the arrays. I.e. starting at CoreNEURON's
5569 // start time. (Multiple calls to psolve append to these arrays.)
5570 // n_pr refers the the number of PlayRecord instances in the vpr array.
5571 // n_trajec refers to the number of trajectories to be recorded on the
5572 // CoreNEURON side and is the size of the types, indices, and varrays.
5573 // n_pr is different from n_trajec when one of the GLineRecord instances has
5574 // a gl_->name that is an expression that contains several range variables.
5575 // Per time step transfer now uses pvars so CoreNEURON scatters values
5576 // to pvars instead of collecting in double array.
5577 void nrnthread_get_trajectory_requests(int tid,
5578  int& bsize,
5579  int& n_pr,
5580  void**& vpr,
5581  int& n_trajec,
5582  int*& types,
5583  int*& indices,
5584  double**& pvars,
5585  double**& varrays) {
5586  if (bsize > 0) { // but would NEURON rather use per time step mode
5587  if (nrn_trajectory_request_per_time_step_) {
5588  bsize = 0;
5589  }
5590  }
5591  n_pr = 0;
5592  n_trajec = 0;
5593  types = NULL;
5594  indices = NULL;
5595  vpr = NULL;
5596  varrays = NULL;
5597  pvars = NULL;
5598  if (tid < nrn_nthread) {
5599  NrnThread& nt = nrn_threads[tid];
5600  auto* fr = net_cvode_instance->fixed_record_;
5601  // allocate
5602  for (auto& pr: *fr) {
5603  if (pr->ith_ == tid) {
5604  if (pr->type() == TvecRecordType || pr->type() == YvecRecordType) {
5605  n_pr++;
5606  n_trajec++;
5607 #if HAVE_IV
5608  } else if (pr->type() == GLineRecordType) {
5609  n_pr++;
5610  if (!pr->pd_) {
5611  GLineRecord* glr = (GLineRecord*) pr;
5612  assert(glr->gl_->expr_);
5613  glr->fill_pd();
5614  if (pr->pd_) {
5615  n_trajec++;
5616  } else {
5617  n_trajec += glr->pd_and_vec_.size();
5618  }
5619  } else {
5620  n_trajec++;
5621  }
5622  } else if (pr->type() == GVectorRecordType) {
5623  GVectorRecord* gvr = (GVectorRecord*) pr;
5624  if (gvr->count()) {
5625  bsize = 0;
5626  n_pr++;
5627  for (int j = 0; j < gvr->count(); ++j) {
5628  if (gvr->pdata(j)) {
5629  n_trajec++;
5630  }
5631  }
5632  }
5633 #endif // HAVE_IV
5634  }
5635  }
5636  }
5637  if (n_pr == 0) {
5638  return;
5639  }
5640  vpr = new void*[n_pr];
5641  types = new int[n_trajec];
5642  indices = new int[n_trajec];
5643  if (bsize > 0) {
5644  varrays = new double*[n_trajec];
5645  } else {
5646  pvars = new double*[n_trajec];
5647  } // if both varrays and pvars are NULL then CoreNEURON will return values every time step
5648  // everything allocated, start over and fill
5649  n_pr = 0;
5650  n_trajec = 0;
5651  for (auto& pr: *fr) {
5652  int err = 0;
5653  if (pr->ith_ == tid) {
5654  if (1) { // buffered or per time step value return
5655  if (pr->type() == TvecRecordType) {
5656  IvocVect* v = ((TvecRecord*) pr)->t_;
5657  err = trajec_buffered(nt,
5658  bsize,
5659  v,
5660  neuron::container::data_handle<double>{
5661  neuron::container::do_not_search, &nt._t},
5662  n_pr++,
5663  pr,
5664  vpr,
5665  n_trajec++,
5666  types,
5667  indices,
5668  pvars,
5669  varrays);
5670  if (err) {
5671  n_pr--;
5672  n_trajec--;
5673  }
5674  } else if (pr->type() == YvecRecordType) {
5675  IvocVect* v = ((YvecRecord*) pr)->y_;
5676  err = trajec_buffered(nt,
5677  bsize,
5678  v,
5679  pr->pd_,
5680  n_pr++,
5681  pr,
5682  vpr,
5683  n_trajec++,
5684  types,
5685  indices,
5686  pvars,
5687  varrays);
5688  if (err) {
5689  n_pr--;
5690  n_trajec--;
5691  }
5692 #if HAVE_IV
5693  } else if (pr->type() == GLineRecordType) {
5694  GLineRecord* glr = (GLineRecord*) pr;
5695  if (pr->pd_) { // glr->gl_->name is an expression resolved to a double*
5696  if (bsize && !glr->v_) {
5697  glr->v_ = new IvocVect(bsize);
5698  }
5699  IvocVect* v = glr->v_;
5700  err = trajec_buffered(nt,
5701  bsize,
5702  v,
5703  pr->pd_,
5704  n_pr++,
5705  pr,
5706  vpr,
5707  n_trajec++,
5708  types,
5709  indices,
5710  pvars,
5711  varrays);
5712  if (err) {
5713  n_pr--;
5714  n_trajec--;
5715  }
5716  } else { // glr->gl_->name expression involves several range variables
5717  int n = n_trajec;
5718  for (auto&& [pd, v]: glr->pd_and_vec_) {
5719  assert(pd);
5720  if (bsize && v == nullptr) {
5721  v = new IvocVect(bsize);
5722  }
5723  // TODO avoid the conversion?
5724  err = trajec_buffered(nt,
5725  bsize,
5726  v,
5727  neuron::container::data_handle<double>{pd},
5728  n_pr,
5729  pr,
5730  vpr,
5731  n_trajec++,
5732  types,
5733  indices,
5734  pvars,
5735  varrays);
5736  if (err) {
5737  break;
5738  }
5739  }
5740  n_pr++;
5741  if (err) { // single error removes entire GLineRecord
5742  n_pr--;
5743  n_trajec = n;
5744  }
5745  }
5746  } else if (pr->type() == GVectorRecordType) {
5747  GVectorRecord* gvr = (GVectorRecord*) pr;
5748  if (gvr->count()) {
5749  int n = n_trajec;
5750  for (int j = 0; j < gvr->count(); ++j) {
5751  if (gvr->pdata(j)) {
5752  err = trajec_buffered(nt,
5753  bsize,
5754  NULL,
5755  gvr->pdata(j),
5756  n_pr,
5757  pr,
5758  vpr,
5759  n_trajec++,
5760  types,
5761  indices,
5762  pvars,
5763  varrays);
5764  if (err) {
5765  break;
5766  }
5767  }
5768  }
5769  n_pr++;
5770  if (err) { // single error removes entire GVectorRecord
5771  n_pr--;
5772  n_trajec = n;
5773  }
5774  }
5775 #endif // HAVE_IV
5776  }
5777  }
5778  }
5779  }
5780  if (n_trajec == 0) { // if errors reduced to 0, clean up
5781  assert(n_pr == 0);
5782  delete[] std::exchange(types, nullptr);
5783  delete[] std::exchange(indices, nullptr);
5784  delete[] std::exchange(vpr, nullptr);
5785  delete[] std::exchange(varrays, nullptr);
5786  delete[] std::exchange(pvars, nullptr);
5787  }
5788 #if 0
5789  printf("nrnthread_get_trajectory_requests tid=%d bsize=%d n_pr=%d n_trajec=%d\n", tid, bsize, n_pr, n_trajec);
5790  int i_trajec = 0;
5791  double* pd;
5792  for (int i=0; i < n_pr; ++i) {
5793  PlayRecord* pr = (PlayRecord*)vpr[i];
5794  pd = pr->pd_;
5795  if (pd) {
5796  printf(" %d %d prtype=%d %p type=%d index=%d\n", i, i_trajec, pr->type(), pd, types[i_trajec], indices[i_trajec]);
5797  i_trajec++;
5798  }else{
5799  assert(pr->type() == GLineRecordType);
5800  GLineRecord* glr = (GLineRecord*)pr;
5801  GLineRecordEData& ed = glr->pd_and_vec_;
5802  i_trajec += ed.size();
5803  }
5804  }
5805 #endif
5806  }
5807 }
5808 
5809 void nrnthread_trajectory_values(int tid, int n_pr, void** vpr, double tt) { //, int n_trajec,
5810  // double* values) {
5811  if (tid < 0) {
5812  return;
5813  }
5814  if (tid < nrn_nthread) {
5815 #if HAVE_IV
5816  ObjectContext obc(NULL); // in case GLineRecord with expression.
5817 #endif // HAVE_IV
5818  nrn_threads[tid]._t = tt;
5819  if (tid == 0) {
5820  t = tt;
5821  }
5822  int flush = 0;
5823  for (int i = 0; i < n_pr; ++i) {
5824  PlayRecord* pr = (PlayRecord*) vpr[i];
5825  pr->continuous(tt);
5826 #if HAVE_IV
5827  if (pr->type() == GVectorRecordType) { // see the movie
5828  flush = 1;
5829  }
5830  }
5831  if (flush) {
5832  Oc oc;
5833  oc.run("screen_update()\n");
5834  }
5835 #else
5836  }
5837 #endif // HAVE_IV
5838  }
5839 }
5840 
5841 // CoreNEURON received pointers to the data of each Vector (resized so that
5842 // the data is long enough to hold the trajectory (tstop/dt). On calling
5843 // this, each Vector needs only be resized to the actual vecsz.
5844 // Note that we have not bothered to fill the variables on the hoc side with
5845 // the last values, though we did fill t.
5846 // In the case where glr->pd_ = NULL, the GraphLine is an expression that
5847 // cannot be interpreted as a pointer and the expression involves one or
5848 // more range variables that individually were resolved into pointers. In
5849 // this case in glr->plot, the relevant Vector elements are copied into those
5850 // pointers and the expression is then evaluated and plotted.
5851 void nrnthread_trajectory_return(int tid, int n_pr, int bsize, int vecsz, void** vpr, double tt) {
5852  if (tid < 0) {
5853  return;
5854  }
5855  if (tid < nrn_nthread) {
5856  nrn_threads[tid]._t = tt;
5857  if (tid == 0) {
5858  t = tt;
5859  }
5860  for (int i = 0; i < n_pr; ++i) {
5861  PlayRecord* pr = (PlayRecord*) vpr[i];
5862  IvocVect* v = NULL;
5863  if (pr->type() == TvecRecordType) {
5864  v = ((TvecRecord*) pr)->t_;
5865  // reserved bsize but only used vecsz. (need non-zeroing resize).
5866  v->resize(v->size() - (bsize - vecsz)); // do not zero
5867  } else if (pr->type() == YvecRecordType) {
5868  v = ((YvecRecord*) pr)->y_;
5869  v->resize(v->size() - (bsize - vecsz)); // do not zero
5870 #if HAVE_IV
5871  } else if (pr->type() == GLineRecordType) {
5872  GLineRecord* glr = (GLineRecord*) pr;
5873  glr->plot(vecsz, tt);
5874 #endif // HAVE_IV
5875  } else {
5876  assert(0);
5877  }
5878  }
5879  }
5880 }
5881 
5882 // factored this out from deliver_net_events so we can
5883 // stay in the cache
5884 void NetCvode::check_thresh(NrnThread* nt) { // for default method
5885  nrn::Instrumentor::phase p_check_threshold("check-threshold");
5886  hoc_Item* pth = p[nt->id].psl_thr_;
5887 
5888  if (pth) { /* only look at ones with a threshold */
5889  hoc_Item* q1;
5890  ITERATE(q1, pth) {
5891  PreSyn* ps = (PreSyn*) VOIDITM(q1);
5892  // only the ones for this thread
5893  if (ps->nt_ == nt) {
5894  if (ps->thvar_) {
5895  ps->check(nt, nt->_t, 1e-10);
5896  }
5897  }
5898  }
5899  }
5900 
5901  for (HTList* wl: wl_list_[nt->id]) {
5902  for (HTList* item = wl->First(); item != wl->End(); item = item->Next()) {
5903  WatchCondition* wc = (WatchCondition*) item;
5904  wc->check(nt, nt->_t);
5905  }
5906  }
5907 }

5909 /** In nrncore_callbacks.cpp **/
5910 extern void nrn2core_transfer_WatchCondition(WatchCondition* wc,
5911  void (*cb)(int, int, int, int, int));
5912 extern "C" {
5913 void nrn2core_transfer_WATCH(void (*cb)(int, int, int, int, int));
5914 }
5915 void nrn2core_transfer_WATCH(void (*cb)(int, int, int, int, int)) {
5916  // should be revisited for possible simplification since wl_list now
5917  // segregated by threads.
5918  for (auto& htlists_of_thread: net_cvode_instance->wl_list_) {
5919  for (HTList* wl: htlists_of_thread) {
5920  for (HTList* item = wl->First(); item != wl->End(); item = item->Next()) {
5921  WatchCondition* wc = (WatchCondition*) item;
5922  nrn2core_transfer_WatchCondition(wc, cb);
5923  }
5924  }
5925  }

5927 
5928 void NetCvode::deliver_net_events(NrnThread* nt) { // for default method
5929  TQItem* q;
5930  double tm, tsav;
5931 #if NRNMPI
5932  if (use_multisend_) {
5933  nrn_multisend_advance();
5934  }
5935 #endif
5936  int tid = nt->id;
5937  tsav = nt->_t;
5938  tm = nt->_t + 0.5 * nt->_dt;
5939 tryagain:
5940  // one of the events on the main queue may be a NetParEvent
5941  // which due to dt round off error can result in an event
5942  // placed on the bin queue to be delivered now, which
5943  // can put 0 delay events on to the main queue. So loop til
5944  // no events. The alternative would be to deliver an idt=0 event
5945  // immediately but that would very much change the sequence
5946  // with respect to what is being done here and it is unclear
5947  // how to fix the value of t there. This can be a do while loop
5948  // but I do not want to affect the case of not using a bin queue.
5949 
5950  if (nrn_use_bin_queue_) {
5951  // it was noticed on binq + compressed spike exchange +
5952  // threads that a transferred event may be languishing in
5953  // the interthread event buffer. Perhaps this is better done
5954  // as a multithread job at the end of nrn_spike_exchange
5955  // instead of every time step --- but here we are
5956  // already in a multithread job, so what is the overhead of
5957  // starting such a small one in nrn_spike_exchange.
5958 #if NRNMPI
5959  extern bool nrn_use_compress_;
5960  if (nrn_use_compress_ && nrn_nthread > 1) {
5961  p[tid].enqueue(this, nt);
5962  }
5963 #endif
5964  while ((q = p[tid].tqe_->dequeue_bin()) != 0) {
5965  DiscreteEvent* db = (DiscreteEvent*) q->data_;
5966 #if PRINT_EVENT
5967  if (print_event_) {
5968  db->pr("binq deliver", nt_t, this);
5969  }
5970 #endif
5971  p[tid].tqe_->release(q);
5972  db->deliver(nt->_t, this, nt);
5973  }
5974  // assert(int(tm/nt->_dt)%1000 == p[tid].tqe_->nshift_);
5975  }
5976 
5977  deliver_events(tm, nt);
5978 
5979  if (nrn_use_bin_queue_) {
5980  if (p[tid].tqe_->top()) {
5981  goto tryagain;
5982  }
5983  p[tid].tqe_->shift_bin(tm);
5984  }
5985  nt->_t = tsav;
5986 }

6286 
6287 void NetCvode::playrec_setup() {
6288  long i, j;
6289  fixed_record_->clear();
6290  fixed_play_->clear();
6291  if (gcv_) {
6292  gcv_->delete_prl();
6293  } else {
6294  lvardtloop(i, j) {
6295  p[i].lcv_[j].delete_prl();
6296  }
6297  }
6298  std::vector<PlayRecord*> to_delete{};
6299  for (auto& pr: *prl_) {
6300  if (!pr->pd_) {
6301  // Presumably the recorded value was invalidated elsewhere, e.g. it
6302  // was a voltage of a deleted node, or a range variable of a deleted
6303  // mechanism instance
6304  to_delete.push_back(pr);
6305  continue;
6306  }
6307  bool b = false;
6308  if (single_) {
6309  pr->install(gcv_);
6310  b = true;
6311  } else {
6312  if (pr->ppobj_ && ob2pntproc(pr->ppobj_)->nvi_) {
6313  pr->install((Cvode*) ob2pntproc(pr->ppobj_)->nvi_);
6314  b = true;
6315  } else {
6316  lvardtloop(i, j) {
6317  Cvode& cv = p[i].lcv_[j];
6318  if (cv.is_owner(pr->pd_)) {
6319  pr->install(&cv);
6320  b = true;
6321  break;
6322  }
6323  }
6324  }
6325  }
6326  if (b == false) {
6327  hoc_execerror("We were unable to associate a PlayRecord item with a RANGE variable",
6328  nullptr);
6329  }
6330  // and need to know the thread owners
6331  if (pr->ppobj_) {
6332  i = PP2NT(ob2pntproc(pr->ppobj_))->id;
6333  } else {
6334  i = owned_by_thread(pr->pd_);
6335  }
6336  if (i < 0) {
6337  hoc_execerror("We were unable to associate a PlayRecord item with a thread", nullptr);
6338  }
6339  pr->ith_ = i;
6340  }
6341  for (auto* pr: to_delete) {
6342  // Destructor should de-register things
6343  delete pr;
6344  }
6345  playrec_change_cnt_ = structure_change_cnt_;
6346 }
6347 
6348 // is a pointer to range variable in this cell
6349 bool Cvode::is_owner(neuron::container::data_handle<double> const& handle) {
6350  int in, it;
6351  for (it = 0; it < nrn_nthread; ++it) {
6352  CvodeThreadData& z = CTD(it);
6353  for (in = 0; in < z.v_node_count_; ++in) {
6354  Node* nd = z.v_node_[in];
6355  if (handle == nd->v_handle()) {
6356  return true;
6357  }
6358  auto* pd = static_cast<double const*>(handle);
6359  Prop* p;
6360  for (p = nd->prop; p; p = p->next) {
6361  if (p->owns(handle)) {
6362  return true;
6363  }
6364  }
6365  if (nd->extnode) {
6366  if (pd >= nd->extnode->v && pd < (nd->extnode->v + nlayer)) {
6367  return true;
6368  }
6369  }
6370  // will need to check the linear mechanisms when there is a cvode
6371  // specific list of them and IDA is allowed for local step method.
6372  }
6373  if (nth_) {
6374  break;
6375  } // lvardt
6376  }
6377  return false;
6378 }
6379 
6380 int NetCvode::owned_by_thread(neuron::container::data_handle<double> const& handle) {
6381  if (nrn_nthread == 1) {
6382  return 0;
6383  }
6384  int in, it;
6385  for (it = 0; it < nrn_nthread; ++it) {
6386  NrnThread& nt = nrn_threads[it];
6387  int i1 = 0;
6388  int i3 = nt.end;
6389  for (in = i1; in < i3; ++in) {
6390  Node* nd = nt._v_node[in];
6391  if (handle == nd->v_handle()) {
6392  return it;
6393  }
6394  for (Prop* p = nd->prop; p; p = p->next) {
6395  if (p->owns(handle)) {
6396  return it;
6397  }
6398  }
6399  if (nd->extnode) {
6400  auto* pd = static_cast<double const*>(handle);
6401  if (pd >= nd->extnode->v && pd < (nd->extnode->v + nlayer)) {
6402  return it;
6403  }
6404  }
6405  // will need to check the line mechanisms when there is a cvode
6406  // specific list of them and IDA is allowed for local step method.
6407  }
6408  }
6409  return -1;
6410 }
6411 
6412 void NetCvode::consist_sec_pd(const char* msg,
6413  Section* sec,
6414  neuron::container::data_handle<double> const& handle) {
6415  int in;
6416  Node* nd;
6417  for (in = -1; in < sec->nnode; ++in) {
6418  if (in == -1) {
6419  nd = sec->parentnode; // in case &v(0)
6420  if (!nd) {
6421  continue;
6422  }
6423  } else {
6424  nd = sec->pnode[in];
6425  }
6426  if (nd->v_handle() == handle) {
6427  return;
6428  }
6429  Prop* p;
6430  auto* const pd = static_cast<double const*>(handle);
6431  for (p = nd->prop; p; p = p->next) {
6432  if (p->owns(handle)) {
6433  return;
6434  }
6435  }
6436  if (nd->extnode) {
6437  if (pd >= nd->extnode->v && pd < (nd->extnode->v + nlayer)) {
6438  return;
6439  }
6440  }
6441  // will need to check the linear mechanisms when there is a cvode
6442  // specific list of them and IDA is allowed for local step method.
6443  }
6444  hoc_execerror(msg,
6445  " pointer not associated with currently accessed section\n\
6446 Use section ... (&var(x)...) intead of ...(&section.var(x)...)\n");
6447 }
6448 
6449 double NetCvode::state_magnitudes() {
6450  if (hoc_is_double_arg(1)) {
6451  int on = (int) chkarg(1, 0, 2);
6452  int i, j;
6453  if (on == 2) {
6454  maxstate_analyse();
6455  } else {
6456  if (gcv_) {
6457  gcv_->activate_maxstate(on ? true : false);
6458  } else {
6459  lvardtloop(i, j) {
6460  p[i].lcv_[j].activate_maxstate(on ? true : false);
6461  }
6462  }
6463  }
6464  return 0.;
6465  } else if (hoc_is_str_arg(1)) {
6466  Symbol* sym = name2sym(gargstr(1));
6467  double dummy;
6468  double* pamax = &dummy;
6469  if (ifarg(2)) {
6470  pamax = hoc_pgetarg(2);
6471  }
6472  return maxstate_analyse(sym, pamax);
6473  } else {
6474  int i, j, n;
6475  Vect* v = vector_arg(1);
6476  if (!cvode_active_) {
6477  v->resize(0);
6478  return 0.;
6479  }
6480  double* vp;
6481  n = 0;
6482  if (gcv_) {
6483  n += gcv_->neq_;
6484  } else {
6485  lvardtloop(i, j) {
6486  n += p[i].lcv_[j].neq_;
6487  }
6488  }
6489  v->resize(n);
6490  vp = vector_vec(v);
6491  int getacor = 0;
6492  if (ifarg(2)) {
6493  getacor = (int) chkarg(2, 0, 1);
6494  }
6495  j = 0;
6496  if (gcv_) {
6497  if (gcv_->maxstate_) {
6498  if (getacor) {
6499  gcv_->maxacor(vp);
6500  } else {
6501  gcv_->maxstate(vp);
6502  }
6503  }
6504  } else {
6505  lvardtloop(i, j) {
6506  Cvode& cv = p[i].lcv_[j];
6507  if (cv.maxstate_) {
6508  if (getacor) {
6509  cv.maxacor(vp + j);
6510  } else {
6511  cv.maxstate(vp + j);
6512  }
6513  }
6514  j += cv.neq_;
6515  }
6516  }
6517  return 0.;
6518  }
6519 }
6520 void NetCvode::maxstate_analyze_1(int it, Cvode& cv, CvodeThreadData& z) {
6521  int j, n;
6522  Symbol* sym;
6523  double* ms;
6524  double* ma;
6525  n = z.nvsize_;
6526  ms = cv.n_vector_data(cv.maxstate_, it);
6527  ma = cv.n_vector_data(cv.maxacor_, it);
6528  auto const hdp = create_hdp(2);
6529  for (j = 0; j < n; ++j) {
6530  sym = hdp.retrieve_sym(static_cast<double*>(z.pv_[j]));
6531  auto msti = mst_->find((void*) sym);
6532  MaxStateItem* msi;
6533  if (msti == mst_->end()) {
6534  msi = new MaxStateItem();
6535  msi->sym_ = sym;
6536  msi->max_ = -1e9;
6537  msi->amax_ = -1e9;
6538  (*mst_)[(void*) sym] = msi;
6539  } else {
6540  msi = msti->second;
6541  }
6542  if (msi->max_ < ms[j]) {
6543  msi->max_ = ms[j];
6544  }
6545  if (msi->amax_ < ma[j]) {
6546  msi->amax_ = ma[j];
6547  }
6548  }
6549 }
6550 
6551 void NetCvode::maxstate_analyse() {
6552  int i, it, j;
6553  Symbol* sym;
6554  if (!mst_) {
6555  int n = 0;
6556  for (sym = hoc_built_in_symlist->first; sym; sym = sym->next) {
6557  ++n;
6558  }
6559  mst_ = new MaxStateTable(3 * n);
6560  }
6561  for (auto ti: *mst_) {
6562  MaxStateItem* msi = ti.second;
6563  msi->max_ = -1e9;
6564  msi->amax_ = -1e9;
6565  }
6566  if (empty_) {
6567  return;
6568  }
6569  statename(0, 2);
6570  if (gcv_) {
6571  for (it = 0; it < nrn_nthread; ++it) {
6572  maxstate_analyze_1(it, *gcv_, gcv_->ctd_[it]);
6573  }
6574  } else {
6575  lvardtloop(i, j) {
6576  Cvode& cv = p[i].lcv_[j];
6577  maxstate_analyze_1(i, cv, cv.ctd_[0]);
6578  }
6579  }
6580 }
6581 
6582 double NetCvode::maxstate_analyse(Symbol* sym, double* pamax) {
6583  if (mst_) {
6584  auto msti = mst_->find((void*) sym);
6585  if (msti != mst_->end()) {
6586  *pamax = msti->second->amax_;
6587  return msti->second->max_;
6588  }
6589  }
6590  *pamax = -1e9;
6591  return -1e9;
6592 }
6593 
6594 static double lvardt_tout_;
6595 
6596 static void lvardt_integrate(neuron::model_sorted_token const& token, NrnThread& ntr) {
6597  auto* const nt = &ntr;
6598  size_t err = NVI_SUCCESS;
6599  int id = nt->id;
6600  NetCvode* nc = net_cvode_instance;
6601  NetCvodeThreadData& p = nc->p[id];
6602  TQueue* tq = p.tq_;
6603  TQueue* tqe = p.tqe_;
6604  double tout = lvardt_tout_;
6605  nt->_stop_stepping = 0;
6606  while (tq->least_t() < tout || tqe->least_t() <= tout) {
6607  err = nc->local_microstep(token, ntr);
6608  if (nt->_stop_stepping) {
6609  nt->_stop_stepping = 0;
6610  return;
6611  }
6612  if (err != NVI_SUCCESS || stoprun) {
6613  return;
6614  }
6615  }
6616  int n = p.nlcv_;
6617  Cvode* lcv = p.lcv_;
6618  if (n)
6619  for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
6620  nc->retreat(tout, lcv + i);
6621  lcv[i].record_continuous();
6622  }
6623  else {
6624  nt->_t = tout;
6625  }
6626 }
6627 
6628 int NetCvode::solve_when_threads(double tout) {
6629  int err = NVI_SUCCESS;
6630  int tid;
6631  double til;
6632  nrn_use_busywait(1); // just a possibility
6633  auto const cache_token = nrn_ensure_model_data_are_sorted();
6634  if (empty_) {
6635  if (tout >= 0.) {
6636  while (nt_t < tout && !stoprun) {
6637  deliver_events_when_threads(tout);
6638  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
6639  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
6640  }
6641  }
6642  if (stoprun == 0) {
6643  nt_t = tout;
6644  }
6645  } else {
6646  if ((til = allthread_least_t(tid)) < 1e10) {
6647  deliver_events_when_threads(til);
6648  } else {
6649  nt_t += 1e6;
6650  }
6651  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
6652  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
6653  }
6654  }
6655  } else if (gcv_) {
6656  if (tout >= 0.) {
6657  while (gcv_->t_ < tout || allthread_least_t(tid) < tout) {
6658  err = global_microstep_when_threads();
6659  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
6660  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
6661  }
6662  if (err != NVI_SUCCESS || stoprun) {
6663  return err;
6664  }
6665  }
6666  retreat(tout, gcv_);
6667  gcv_->record_continuous();
6668  } else {
6669  // advance or initialized
6670  double tc = gcv_->t_;
6671  initialized_ = false;
6672  while (gcv_->t_ <= tc && !initialized_) {
6673  err = global_microstep_when_threads();
6674  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
6675  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
6676  }
6677  if (err != NVI_SUCCESS || stoprun) {
6678  return err;
6679  }
6680  }
6681  }
6682  } else { // lvardt
6683  if (tout >= 0.) {
6684  // Each thread could integrate independently to tout
6685  // as long as no thread got more than
6686  // a minimum delay interval ahead of any other.
6687  // For now just integrate by min delay intervals.
6688  lvardt_tout_ = tout;
6689  while (nt_t < tout) {
6690  nrn_multithread_job(cache_token, lvardt_integrate);
6691  if (nrn_allthread_handle) {
6692  (*nrn_allthread_handle)();
6693  }
6694  if (err != NVI_SUCCESS || stoprun) {
6695  return err;
6696  }
6697  int tid;
6698  allthread_least_t(tid);
6699  }
6700  } else {
6701  // nthread>1 is more or less purposeless if we mean
6702  // that only the least cvode of all threads advances.
6703  // (which is required if minimum delay = 0)
6704  if (nrn_nthread > 1) {
6705  hoc_execerror("Lvardt method from fadvance()",
6706  "presently limited to single thread.");
6707  }
6708  }
6709  }
6710  nrn_use_busywait(0);
6711  t = nt_t;
6712  dt = nt_dt;
6713  return err;
6714 }
6715 
6716 static void* deliver_for_thread(NrnThread* nt) {
6717  NetCvode* nc = net_cvode_instance;
6718  NetCvodeThreadData& d = nc->p[nt->id];
6719  TQItem* q = d.tqe_->least();
6720  DiscreteEvent* de = (DiscreteEvent*) q->data_;
6721  double tt = q->t_;
6722  d.tqe_->remove(q);
6723 #if PRINT_EVENT
6724  if (nc->print_event_) {
6725  de->pr("deliver", tt, nc);
6726  }
6727 #endif
6728  de->deliver(tt, nc, nt);
6729  return 0;
6730 }
6731 
6732 void NetCvode::deliver_events_when_threads(double til) {
6733  // printf("deliver_events til %20.15g\n", til);
6734  int tid;
6735  while (allthread_least_t(tid) <= til) {
6736  STATISTICS(deliver_cnt_);
6737  nrn_onethread_job(tid, deliver_for_thread);
6738  if (stoprun || nrn_allthread_handle) {
6739  return;
6740  }
6741  }
6742 }
6743 
6744 int NetCvode::global_microstep_when_threads() {
6745  int err = NVI_SUCCESS;
6746  int tid;
6747  double tt = allthread_least_t(tid);
6748  double tdiff = tt - gcv_->t_;
6749  if (tdiff <= 0) {
6750  // since events do not internally retreat with the
6751  // global step, we should already be at the event time
6752  // if this is too strict, we could use eps(list_->t_).
6753  // if (tdiff != 0.0) { printf("tdiff=%g\n", tdiff); }
6754  assert(tdiff == 0.0 || (gcv_->tstop_begin_ <= tt && tt <= gcv_->tstop_end_));
6755  deliver_events_when_threads(tt);
6756  } else {
6757  err = gcv_->handle_step(nrn_ensure_model_data_are_sorted(), this, tt);
6758  }
6759  if ((tt = allthread_least_t(tid)) < gcv_->t_) {
6760  gcv_->interpolate(tt);
6761  }
6762  return err;
6763 }
6764 
6765 void* nrn_interthread_enqueue(NrnThread* nt) {
6766  net_cvode_instance->p[nt->id].enqueue(net_cvode_instance, nt);
6767  return 0;
6768 }
6769 
6770 void NetCvode::set_enqueueing() {
6771  MUTLOCK
6772  enqueueing_ = 1;
6773  MUTUNLOCK
6774 }
6775 
6776 double NetCvode::allthread_least_t(int& tid) {
6777  // reduce (take minimum) of p[i].tqe_->least_t()
6778  double tt, min = 1e50;
6779  // setting enqueueing_ in interthread_send was a race. Logically it is not
6780  // needed. It is not clear if higher performance would result in having
6781  // a MUTEX for the NetCvode instance but that is the current implementation
6782  // instead of commenting out the enqueuing related lines.
6783  if (enqueueing_) {
6784  nrn_multithread_job(nrn_interthread_enqueue);
6785  enqueueing_ = 0;
6786  }
6787  for (int id = 0; id < pcnt_; ++id) {
6788  tt = p[id].tqe_->least_t();
6789  if (tt < min) {
6790  tid = id;
6791  min = tt;
6792  }
6793  }
6794  return min;
6795 }
